162 const char* gce_ErrorStatusText(gce_ErrorType et)
163 {
164  switch (et)
165  {
166  case gce_Done:
167  return "Construction was successful";
168  case gce_ConfusedPoints:
169  return "Two points are coincident";
170  case gce_NegativeRadius:
171  return "Radius value is negative";
172  case gce_ColinearPoints:
173  return "Three points are collinear";
174  case gce_IntersectionError:
175  return "Intersection cannot be computed";
176  case gce_NullAxis:
177  return "Axis is undefined";
178  case gce_NullAngle:
179  return "Angle value is invalid (usually null)";
180  case gce_NullRadius:
181  return "Radius is null";
182  case gce_InvertAxis:
183  return "Axis value is invalid";
184  case gce_BadAngle:
185  return "Angle value is invalid";
186  case gce_InvertRadius:
187  return "Radius value is incorrect (usually with respect to another radius)";
188  case gce_NullFocusLength:
189  return "Focal distance is null";
190  case gce_NullVector:
191  return "Vector is null";
192  case gce_BadEquation:
193  return "Coefficients are incorrect (applies to the equation of a geometric object)";
194  default:
195  return "Creation of geometry failed";
196  }
197 }

210 bool Geometry::hasSameExtensions(const Geometry& other) const
211 {
212  // We skip non persistent extension while doing comparison. Not sure if
213  // this will cause any problem.
214  size_t index = 0;
215  for (const auto& ext : extensions) {
216  if (auto persistExt =
217  Base::freecad_dynamic_cast<const GeometryPersistenceExtension>(ext.get())) {
218  for (; index < other.extensions.size(); ++index) {
219  if (auto extOther = Base::freecad_dynamic_cast<const GeometryPersistenceExtension>(
220  other.extensions[index].get())) {
221  if (!persistExt->isSame(*extOther)) {
222  return false;
223  }
224  break;
225  }
226  }
227  if (index >= other.extensions.size()) {
228  return false;
229  }
230  ++index;
231  }
232  }
233  for (; index < other.extensions.size(); ++index) {
234  if (Base::freecad_dynamic_cast<const GeometryPersistenceExtension>(
235  other.extensions[index].get())) {
236  return false;
237  }
238  }
239  return true;
240 }

248 std::unique_ptr<Geometry> Geometry::fromShape(const TopoDS_Shape &shape, bool silent)
249 {
250  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> geom;
251 
252  if (shape.IsNull()) {
253  if(!silent)
254  throw Base::ValueError("Null shape");
255  return geom;
256  }
257 
258  switch (shape.ShapeType()) {
259  case TopAbs_VERTEX: {
260  gp_Pnt p = BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopoDS::Vertex(shape));
261  geom = std::make_unique<GeomPoint>(Base::Vector3d(p.X(),p.Y(),p.Z()));
262  break;
263  }
264  case TopAbs_EDGE: {
265  const TopoDS_Edge& e = TopoDS::Edge(shape);
266  BRepAdaptor_Curve adapt(e);
267  geom = makeFromCurveAdaptor(adapt, silent);
268  break;
269  }
270  case TopAbs_FACE: {
271  const TopoDS_Face& f = TopoDS::Face(shape);
272  BRepAdaptor_Surface adapt(f);
273  geom = makeFromSurfaceAdaptor(adapt, silent);
274  break;
275  }
276  default:
277  if(!silent)
278  FC_THROWM(Base::TypeError, "Unsupported shape type " << TopoShape::shapeName(shape.ShapeType()));
279  }
280  return geom;
281 }
282 
283 void Geometry::Save(Base::Writer &writer) const
284 {
285  // We always store an extension array even if empty, so that restoring is consistent.
286 
287  // Get the number of persistent extensions
288  int counter = 0;
289  for(const auto& att : extensions) {
290  if(att->isDerivedFrom(Part::GeometryPersistenceExtension::getClassTypeId()))
291  counter++;
292  }
293 
294  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "<GeoExtensions count=\"" << counter << "\">" << std::endl;
295 
296  writer.incInd();
297 
298  for(const auto& att : extensions) {
299  if(att->isDerivedFrom(Part::GeometryPersistenceExtension::getClassTypeId()))
300  std::static_pointer_cast<Part::GeometryPersistenceExtension>(att)->Save(writer);
301  }
302 
303  writer.decInd();
304  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "</GeoExtensions>" << std::endl;
305 }
306 
307 void Geometry::Restore(Base::XMLReader &reader)
308 {
309  // In legacy file format, there are no extensions and there is a construction XML tag
310  // In the new format, this is migrated into extensions, and we get an array with extensions
311  reader.readElement();
312 
313  if(strcmp(reader.localName(),"GeoExtensions") == 0) { // new format
314 
315  long count = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("count");
316 
317  for (long index = 0; index < count; index++) {
318  reader.readElement("GeoExtension");
319  const char* TypeName = reader.getAttribute("type");
320  Base::Type type = Base::Type::fromName(TypeName);
321  auto *newExtension = static_cast<GeometryPersistenceExtension *>(type.createInstance());
322  if (newExtension) {
323  newExtension->Restore(reader);
324 
325  extensions.push_back(std::shared_ptr<GeometryExtension>(newExtension));
326  }
327  else {
328  Base::Console().Warning("Cannot restore geometry extension of type: %s\n", TypeName);
329  }
330  }
331 
332  reader.readEndElement("GeoExtensions");
333  }
334  else if(strcmp(reader.localName(),"Construction") == 0) { // legacy
335 
336  bool construction = (int)reader.getAttributeAsInteger("value") != 0;
337 
338  // prepare migration
339  if(!this->hasExtension(GeometryMigrationExtension::getClassTypeId()))
340  this->setExtension(std::make_unique<GeometryMigrationExtension>());
341 
342  auto ext = std::static_pointer_cast<GeometryMigrationExtension>(this->getExtension(GeometryMigrationExtension::getClassTypeId()).lock());
343 
344  ext->setMigrationType(GeometryMigrationExtension::Construction);
345  ext->setConstruction(construction);
346 
347  }
348 
349 }

356 std::vector<std::weak_ptr<const GeometryExtension>> Geometry::getExtensions() const
357 {
358  std::vector<std::weak_ptr<const GeometryExtension>> wp;
359 
360  for (auto& ext : extensions) {
361  wp.push_back(ext);
362  }
363 
364  return wp;
365 }

367 bool Geometry::hasExtension(const Base::Type & type) const
368 {
369  return std::any_of(extensions.begin(),
370  extensions.end(),
371  [type](auto geoExt) {
372  return geoExt->getTypeId() == type;
373  });
374 }
375 
376 bool Geometry::hasExtension(const std::string & name) const
377 {
378  return std::any_of(extensions.begin(),
379  extensions.end(),
380  [name](auto geoExt) {
381  return geoExt->getName() == name;
382  });
383 }
384 
385 std::weak_ptr<GeometryExtension> Geometry::getExtension(const Base::Type & type)
386 {
387  for(const auto& ext : extensions) {
388  if(ext->getTypeId() == type)
389  return ext;
390  }
391 
392  throw Base::ValueError("No geometry extension of the requested type.");
393 }
394 
395 std::weak_ptr<GeometryExtension> Geometry::getExtension(const std::string & name)
396 {
397  for(const auto& ext : extensions) {
398  if(ext->getName() == name)
399  return ext;
400  }
401 
402  throw Base::ValueError("No geometry extension with the requested name.");
403 }

415 
416 void Geometry::setExtension(std::unique_ptr<GeometryExtension> && geoext )
417 {
418  bool hasext=false;
419 
420  for( auto & ext : extensions) {
421  // if same type and name, this modifies the existing extension.
422  if( ext->getTypeId() == geoext->getTypeId() &&
423  ext->getName() == geoext->getName()){
424  ext = std::move( geoext );
425  ext->notifyAttachment(this);
426  hasext = true;
427  break;
428  }
429  }
430 
431  if(!hasext) { // new type-name unique id, so add.
432  extensions.push_back(std::move( geoext ));
433  extensions.back()->notifyAttachment(this);
434  }
435 }
436 
437 void Geometry::deleteExtension(const Base::Type & type)
438 {
439  extensions.erase(
440  std::remove_if( extensions.begin(),
441  extensions.end(),
442  [&type](const std::shared_ptr<GeometryExtension>& ext){
443  return ext->getTypeId() == type;
444  }),
445  extensions.end());
446 }
447 
448 void Geometry::deleteExtension(const std::string & name)
449 {
450  extensions.erase(
451  std::remove_if( extensions.begin(),
452  extensions.end(),
453  [&name](const std::shared_ptr<GeometryExtension>& ext){
454  return ext->getName() == name;
455  }),
456  extensions.end());
457 }

460 void Geometry::createNewTag()
461 {
462  // Initialize a random number generator, to avoid Valgrind false positives.
463  // The random number generator is not threadsafe so we guard it. See
464  // https://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_62_0/libs/uuid/uuid.html#Design%20notes
465  static boost::mt19937 ran;
466  static bool seeded = false;
467  static boost::mutex random_number_mutex;
468 
469  boost::lock_guard<boost::mutex> guard(random_number_mutex);
470 
471  if (!seeded) {
472  ran.seed(static_cast<unsigned int>(std::time(nullptr)));
473  seeded = true;
474  }
475  static boost::uuids::basic_random_generator<boost::mt19937> gen(&ran);
476 
477  tag = gen();
478 }

480 void Geometry::assignTag(const Part::Geometry * geo)
481 {
482  if(geo->getTypeId() == this->getTypeId())
483  this->tag = geo->tag;
484  else
485  throw Base::TypeError("Geometry tag can not be assigned as geometry types do not match.");
486 }
487 
488 void Geometry::copyNonTag(const Part::Geometry* src)
489 {
490  for (auto& ext : src->extensions) {
491  this->extensions.push_back(ext->copy());
492  extensions.back()->notifyAttachment(this);
493  }
494 }

496 Geometry *Geometry::clone() const
497 {
498  Geometry* cpy = this->copy();
499  cpy->tag = this->tag;
500 
501  // class copy is responsible for copying extensions
502 
503  return cpy;
504 }

512 void Geometry::mirror(const Base::Vector3d& point, const Base::Vector3d& dir) const
513 {
514  gp_Ax1 ax1(gp_Pnt(point.x,point.y,point.z), gp_Dir(dir.x,dir.y,dir.z));
515  handle()->Mirror(ax1);
516 }
517 
518 void Geometry::rotate(const Base::Placement& plm) const
519 {
520  Base::Rotation rot(plm.getRotation());
521  Base::Vector3d pnt, dir;
522 
523  double angle;
524 
525  rot.getValue(dir, angle);
526  pnt = plm.getPosition();
527 
528  gp_Ax1 ax1(gp_Pnt(pnt.x,pnt.y,pnt.z), gp_Dir(dir.x,dir.y,dir.z));
529  handle()->Rotate(ax1, angle);
530 }
531 
532 void Geometry::scale(const Base::Vector3d& vec, double scale) const
533 {
534  gp_Pnt pnt(vec.x, vec.y, vec.z);
535  handle()->Scale(pnt, scale);
536 }
537 
538 void Geometry::transform(const Base::Matrix4D& mat) const
539 {
540  gp_Trsf trf;
541  trf.SetValues(mat[0][0],mat[0][1],mat[0][2],mat[0][3],
542  mat[1][0],mat[1][1],mat[1][2],mat[1][3],
543  mat[2][0],mat[2][1],mat[2][2],mat[2][3]);
544  handle()->Transform(trf);
545 }
546 
547 void Geometry::translate(const Base::Vector3d& vec) const
548 {
549  gp_Vec trl(vec.x, vec.y, vec.z);
550  handle()->Translate(trl);
551 }

614 void GeomPoint::Save(Base::Writer &writer) const
615 {
616  // save the attributes of the father class
617  Geometry::Save(writer);
618 
619  Base::Vector3d Point = getPoint();
620  writer.Stream()
621  << writer.ind()
622  << "<GeomPoint "
623  << "X=\"" << Point.x <<
624  "\" Y=\"" << Point.y <<
625  "\" Z=\"" << Point.z <<
626  "\"/>" << std::endl;
627 }
628 
629 void GeomPoint::Restore(Base::XMLReader &reader)
630 {
631  // read the attributes of the father class
632  Geometry::Restore(reader);
633 
634  double X,Y,Z;
635  // read my Element
636  reader.readElement("GeomPoint");
637  // get the value of my Attribute
638  X = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("X");
639  Y = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("Y");
640  Z = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("Z");
641 
642  // set the read geometry
643  setPoint(Base::Vector3d(X,Y,Z) );
644 }

646 PyObject *GeomPoint::getPyObject()
647 {
648  return new PointPy(new GeomPoint(getPoint()));
649 }
650 
651 bool GeomPoint::isSame(const Geometry &other, double tol, double) const
652 {
653  return other.getTypeId() == getTypeId()
654  && Base::DistanceP2(dynamic_cast<const GeomPoint &>(other).getPoint(),getPoint()) <= tol*tol;
655 }

672 // Copied from OCC BRepBndLib_1.cxx
673 //=======================================================================
674 // Function : IsLinear
675 // purpose : Returns TRUE if theC is line-like.
676 //=======================================================================
677 static Standard_Boolean IsLinear(const Adaptor3d_Curve& theC)
678 {
679  const GeomAbs_CurveType aCT = theC.GetType();
680  if(aCT == GeomAbs_OffsetCurve)
681  {
682  return IsLinear(GeomAdaptor_Curve(theC.OffsetCurve()->BasisCurve()));
683  }
684 
685  if((aCT == GeomAbs_BSplineCurve) || (aCT == GeomAbs_BezierCurve))
686  {
687  // Indeed, curves with C0-continuity and degree==1, may be
688  // represented with set of points. It will be possible made
689  // in the future.
690 
691  return ((theC.Degree() == 1) &&
692  (theC.Continuity() != GeomAbs_C0));
693  }
694 
695  if(aCT == GeomAbs_Line)
696  {
697  return Standard_True;
698  }
699 
700  return Standard_False;
701 }
702 
703 bool GeomCurve::isLinear(Base::Vector3d *dir, Base::Vector3d *base) const
704 {
705  Handle(Geom_Curve) curve = Handle(Geom_Curve)::DownCast(handle());
706  return isLinear(curve, dir, base);
707 }
708 
709 bool GeomCurve::isLinear(const Handle(Geom_Curve) &curve, Base::Vector3d *dir, Base::Vector3d *base)
710 {
711  GeomAdaptor_Curve adaptor(curve);
712  if (!IsLinear(adaptor))
713  return false;
714 
715  if (dir || base) {
716  if (adaptor.GetType() == GeomAbs_Line) {
717  // Special treatment of Geom_Line because it is infinite
718  Handle(Geom_Line) curv = Handle(Geom_Line)::DownCast(curve);
719  if (base) {
720  gp_Pnt Pos = curv->Lin().Location();
721  *base = Base::Vector3d(Pos.X(), Pos.Y(), Pos.Z());
722  }
723  if (dir) {
724  gp_Dir Dir = curv->Lin().Direction();
725  *dir = Base::Vector3d(Dir.X(), Dir.Y(), Dir.Z());
726  }
727  return true;
728  }
729  try {
730  GeomLProp_CLProps prop1(curve,curve->FirstParameter(),0,Precision::Confusion());
731  GeomLProp_CLProps prop2(curve,curve->LastParameter(),0,Precision::Confusion());
732  const gp_Pnt &p1 = prop1.Value();
733  const gp_Pnt &p2 = prop2.Value();
734  if (base)
735  *base = Base::Vector3d(p1.X(), p1.Y(), p1.Z());
736  if (dir)
737  *dir = Base::Vector3d(p2.X() - p1.X(), p2.Y() - p1.Y(), p2.Z() - p1.Z());
738  }
739  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
740  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
741  }
742  }
743  return true;
744 }
745 
746 GeomLine* GeomCurve::toLine(KeepTag clone) const
747 {
748  if (!isLinear())
749  return nullptr;
750 
751  auto p1 = pointAtParameter(getFirstParameter());
752  auto p2 = pointAtParameter(getLastParameter());
753  auto res = new GeomLine(p1, p2-p1);
754  res->copyNonTag(this);
755  if (clone == CopyTag) {
756  res->tag = this->tag;
757  }
758  return res;
759 }
760 
761 GeomLineSegment* GeomCurve::toLineSegment(KeepTag clone) const
762 {
763  if (!isLinear())
764  return nullptr;
765 
766  Base::Vector3d start, end;
767  if (isDerivedFrom(GeomBoundedCurve::getClassTypeId())) {
768  start = dynamic_cast<const GeomBoundedCurve*>(this)->getStartPoint();
769  end = dynamic_cast<const GeomBoundedCurve*>(this)->getEndPoint();
770  } else {
771  start = pointAtParameter(getFirstParameter());
772  end = pointAtParameter(getLastParameter());
773  }
774  auto res = new GeomLineSegment;
775  res->setPoints(start, end);
776  res->copyNonTag(this);
777  if (clone == CopyTag) {
778  res->tag = this->tag;
779  }
780  return res;
781 }

784 {
785  ShapeConstruct_Curve scc;
786  Handle(Geom_Curve) c = Handle(Geom_Curve)::DownCast(handle());
787  Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve) spline = scc.ConvertToBSpline(c, first, last, Precision::Confusion());
788  if (spline.IsNull())
789  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,"Conversion to B-spline failed")
790  return new GeomBSplineCurve(spline);
791 }

867 bool GeomCurve::normalAt(double u, Base::Vector3d& dir) const
868 {

870

875  prop.Normal(gdir);
876  dir = Base::Vector3d(gdir.X(), gdir.Y(), gdir.Z());
877

879  }
880  }
881  catch (const LProp_NotDefined&) {
882  dir.Set(0,0,0);
883  return false;
884  }
885  catch (Standard_Failure& exc) {
886  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, exc.GetMessageString())
887  }
888 
889  return false;
890 }

900 bool GeomCurve::intersect( const GeomCurve *curve,
901  std::vector<std::pair<Base::Vector3d, Base::Vector3d>>& points,
902  double tol) const
903 {
904  Handle(Geom_Curve) curve1 = Handle(Geom_Curve)::DownCast(handle());
905  Handle(Geom_Curve) curve2 = Handle(Geom_Curve)::DownCast(curve->handle());
906 
907  if(!curve1.IsNull() && !curve2.IsNull()) {
908  return intersect(curve1,curve2,points, tol);
909  }
910  else
911  return false;
912 
913 }
914 
915 bool GeomCurve::intersect(const Handle(Geom_Curve)& curve1, const Handle(Geom_Curve)& curve2,
916  std::vector<std::pair<Base::Vector3d, Base::Vector3d>>& points,
917  double tol)
918 {
919  // https://forum.freecad.org/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=31700
920  if (curve1->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_BoundedCurve)) &&
921  curve2->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_BoundedCurve))){
922 
923  Handle(Geom_BoundedCurve) bcurve1 = Handle(Geom_BoundedCurve)::DownCast(curve1);
924  Handle(Geom_BoundedCurve) bcurve2 = Handle(Geom_BoundedCurve)::DownCast(curve2);
925 
926  gp_Pnt c1s = bcurve1->StartPoint();
927  gp_Pnt c2s = bcurve2->StartPoint();
928  gp_Pnt c1e = bcurve1->EndPoint();
929  gp_Pnt c2e = bcurve2->EndPoint();
930 
931  auto checkendpoints = [&points,tol]( gp_Pnt p1, gp_Pnt p2) {
932  if(p1.Distance(p2) < tol)
933  points.emplace_back(Base::Vector3d(p1.X(),p1.Y(),p1.Z()),Base::Vector3d(p2.X(),p2.Y(),p2.Z()));
934  };
935 
936  checkendpoints(c1s,c2s);
937  checkendpoints(c1s,c2e);
938  checkendpoints(c1e,c2s);
939  checkendpoints(c1e,c2e);
940 
941  }
942 
943  try {
944 
945  GeomAPI_ExtremaCurveCurve intersector(curve1, curve2);
946 
947  if (intersector.NbExtrema() == 0 || intersector.LowerDistance() > tol) {
948  // No intersection
949  return false;
950  }
951 
952  for (int index = 1; index <= intersector.NbExtrema(); index++) {
953  if (intersector.Distance(index) > tol)
954  continue;
955 
956  gp_Pnt p1, p2;
957  intersector.Points(index, p1, p2);
958  points.emplace_back(Base::Vector3d(p1.X(),p1.Y(),p1.Z()),Base::Vector3d(p2.X(),p2.Y(),p2.Z()));
959  }
960  }
961  catch (Standard_Failure& exc) {
962  // Yes Extrema finding failed, but if we got an intersection then go on with it
963  if(!points.empty())
964  return !points.empty();
965  else
966  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,exc.GetMessageString())
967  }
968 
969 
970  return !points.empty();
971 }
972 
973 bool GeomCurve::closestParameter(const Base::Vector3d& point, double &u) const
974 {
975  Handle(Geom_Curve) curve = Handle(Geom_Curve)::DownCast(handle());
976  try {
977  if (!curve.IsNull()) {
978  gp_Pnt pnt(point.x,point.y,point.z);
979  GeomAPI_ProjectPointOnCurve ppc(pnt, curve);
980  u = ppc.LowerDistanceParameter();
981  return true;
982  }
983  }
984  catch (StdFail_NotDone& exc) {
985  if (curve->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_BoundedCurve))){
986  Base::Vector3d firstpoint = this->pointAtParameter(curve->FirstParameter());
987  Base::Vector3d lastpoint = this->pointAtParameter(curve->LastParameter());
988 
989  if((firstpoint-point).Length() < (lastpoint-point).Length())
990  u = curve->FirstParameter();
991  else
992  u = curve->LastParameter();
993  }
994  else
995  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, exc.GetMessageString())
996 
997  return true;
998  }
999  catch (Standard_Failure& exc) {
1000  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, exc.GetMessageString())
1001  }
1002 
1003  return false;
1004 }
1005 
1006 bool GeomCurve::closestParameterToBasisCurve(const Base::Vector3d& point, double &u) const
1007 {
1008  Handle(Geom_Curve) curve = Handle(Geom_Curve)::DownCast(handle());
1009 
1010  if (curve->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_TrimmedCurve))){
1011  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) tc = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast(handle());
1012  Handle(Geom_Curve) bc = tc->BasisCurve();
1013  try {
1014  if (!bc.IsNull()) {
1015  gp_Pnt pnt(point.x,point.y,point.z);
1016  GeomAPI_ProjectPointOnCurve ppc(pnt, bc);
1017  u = ppc.LowerDistanceParameter();
1018  return true;
1019  }
1020  }
1021  catch (Standard_Failure& exc) {
1022  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, exc.GetMessageString())
1023  }
1024 
1025  return false;
1026  }
1027  else {
1028  return this->closestParameter(point, u);
1029  }
1030 }

1132 GeomBezierCurve::GeomBezierCurve()
1133 {
1134  TColgp_Array1OfPnt poles(1,2);
1135  poles(1) = gp_Pnt(0.0,0.0,0.0);
1136  poles(2) = gp_Pnt(0.0,0.0,1.0);
1137  Handle(Geom_BezierCurve) bezier = new Geom_BezierCurve(poles);
1138  this->myCurve = bezier;
1139 }

1145 
1146 GeomBezierCurve::GeomBezierCurve( const std::vector<Base::Vector3d>& poles, const std::vector<double>& weights)
1147 {
1148  if (poles.size() != weights.size())
1149  throw Base::ValueError("poles and weights mismatch");
1150 
1151  TColgp_Array1OfPnt poleArray(1,poles.size());
1152  TColStd_Array1OfReal weightArray(1,poles.size());
1153  for (std::size_t index = 1; index <= poles.size(); index++) {
1154  poleArray.SetValue(index, gp_Pnt(poles[index-1].x,poles[index-1].y,poles[index-1].z));
1155  weightArray.SetValue(index, weights[index-1]);
1156  }
1157  this->myCurve = new Geom_BezierCurve (poleArray, weightArray);
1158 }

1165 }

1178 
1179 std::vector<Base::Vector3d> GeomBezierCurve::getPoles() const
1180 {
1181  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> poles;
1182  poles.reserve(myCurve->NbPoles());
1183  TColgp_Array1OfPnt poleArray(1,myCurve->NbPoles());
1184  myCurve->Poles(poleArray);
1185 
1186  for (Standard_Integer index=poleArray.Lower(); index<=poleArray.Upper(); index++) {
1187  const gp_Pnt& pnt = poleArray(index);
1188  poles.emplace_back(pnt.X(), pnt.Y(), pnt.Z());
1189  }
1190  return poles;
1191 }
1192 
1193 std::vector<double> GeomBezierCurve::getWeights() const
1194 {
1195  std::vector<double> weights;
1196  weights.reserve(myCurve->NbPoles());
1197  TColStd_Array1OfReal weightArray(1,myCurve->NbPoles());
1198  myCurve->Weights(weightArray);
1199 
1200  for (Standard_Integer index=weightArray.Lower(); index<=weightArray.Upper(); index++) {
1201  const Standard_Real& real = weightArray(index);
1202  weights.push_back(real);
1203  }
1204  return weights;
1205 }

1213 void GeomBezierCurve::Save(Base::Writer& writer) const
1214 {
1215  // save the attributes of the father class
1216  GeomCurve::Save(writer);
1217 
1218  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> poles = this->getPoles();
1219  std::vector<double> weights = this->getWeights();
1220 
1221  writer.Stream()
1222  << writer.ind()
1223  << "<BezierCurve "
1224  << "PolesCount=\"" << poles.size() <<
1225  "\">" << std::endl;
1226 
1227  writer.incInd();
1228 
1229  std::vector<Base::Vector3d>::const_iterator itp;
1230  std::vector<double>::const_iterator itw;
1231 
1232  for (itp = poles.begin(), itw = weights.begin(); itp != poles.end() && itw != weights.end(); ++itp, ++itw) {
1233  writer.Stream()
1234  << writer.ind()
1235  << "<Pole "
1236  << "X=\"" << (*itp).x <<
1237  "\" Y=\"" << (*itp).y <<
1238  "\" Z=\"" << (*itp).z <<
1239  "\" Weight=\"" << (*itw) <<
1240  "\"/>" << std::endl;
1241  }
1242 
1243  writer.decInd();
1244  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "</BezierCurve>" << std::endl ;
1245 }
1246 
1247 void GeomBezierCurve::Restore(Base::XMLReader& reader)
1248 {
1249  // read the attributes of the father class
1250  GeomCurve::Restore(reader);
1251 
1252  reader.readElement("BezierCurve");
1253  // get the value of my attribute
1254  int polescount = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("PolesCount");
1255 
1256  TColgp_Array1OfPnt poleArray(1,polescount);
1257  TColStd_Array1OfReal weightArray(1,polescount);
1258 
1259  for (int index = 1; index <= polescount; index++) {
1260  reader.readElement("Pole");
1261  double X = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("X");
1262  double Y = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("Y");
1263  double Z = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("Z");
1264  double W = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("Weight");
1265  poleArray.SetValue(index, gp_Pnt(X,Y,Z));
1266  weightArray.SetValue(index, W);
1267  }
1268 
1269  reader.readEndElement("BezierCurve");
1270 
1271  try {
1272  Handle(Geom_BezierCurve) bezier = new Geom_BezierCurve(poleArray, weightArray);
1273 
1274  if (!bezier.IsNull())
1275  this->myCurve = bezier;
1276  else
1277  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,"BezierCurve restore failed")
1278  }
1279  catch (Standard_Failure& exc) {
1280 
1281  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, exc.GetMessageString())
1282  }
1283 }
1284 
1285 PyObject *GeomBezierCurve::getPyObject()
1286 {
1287  return new BezierCurvePy(dynamic_cast<GeomBezierCurve*>(this->clone()));
1288 }
1289 
1290 bool GeomBezierCurve::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double) const
1291 {
1292  if(_other.getTypeId() != getTypeId())
1293  return false;
1294 
1295  auto &other = dynamic_cast<const GeomBezierCurve &>(_other);
1296 
1297  Standard_Integer c = myCurve->NbPoles();
1298  if(c!= other.myCurve->NbPoles())
1299  return false;
1300 
1301  double tol2 = tol*tol;
1302  for(Standard_Integer index =1; index <=c; ++index) {
1303  if(myCurve->Pole(index).SquareDistance(other.myCurve->Pole(index)) > tol2
1304  || fabs(myCurve->Weight(index) - other.myCurve->Weight(index)) > tol)
1305  return false;
1306  }
1307  return true;
1308 }

1312 TYPESYSTEM_SOURCE(Part::GeomBSplineCurve,Part::GeomBoundedCurve)
1313 
1314 GeomBSplineCurve::GeomBSplineCurve()
1315 {
1316  TColgp_Array1OfPnt poles(1,2);
1317  poles(1) = gp_Pnt(0.0,0.0,0.0);
1318  poles(2) = gp_Pnt(1.0,0.0,0.0);
1319 
1320  TColStd_Array1OfReal knots(1,2);
1321  knots(1) = 0.0;
1322  knots(2) = 1.0;
1323 
1324  TColStd_Array1OfInteger mults(1,2);
1325  mults(1) = 2;
1326  mults(2) = 2;
1327 
1328  this->myCurve = new Geom_BSplineCurve(poles, knots, mults, 1);
1329 }
1330 
1331 GeomBSplineCurve::GeomBSplineCurve(const Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve)& b)
1332 {
1333  setHandle(b);
1334 }
1335 
1336 GeomBSplineCurve::GeomBSplineCurve( const std::vector<Base::Vector3d>& poles, const std::vector<double>& weights,
1337  const std::vector<double>& knots, const std::vector<int>& multiplicities,
1338  int degree, bool periodic, bool checkrational)
1339 {
1340  if (poles.size() != weights.size())
1341  throw Base::ValueError("poles and weights mismatch");
1342 
1343  if (knots.size() != multiplicities.size())
1344  throw Base::ValueError("knots and multiplicities mismatch");
1345 
1346  TColgp_Array1OfPnt p(1,poles.size());
1347  TColStd_Array1OfReal w(1,poles.size());
1348  TColStd_Array1OfReal k(1,knots.size());
1349  TColStd_Array1OfInteger m(1,knots.size());
1350 
1351  for (std::size_t index = 1; index <= poles.size(); index++) {
1352  p.SetValue(index, gp_Pnt(poles[index -1].x,poles[index -1].y,poles[index -1].z));
1353  w.SetValue(index, weights[index -1]);
1354  }
1355 
1356  for (std::size_t index = 1; index <= knots.size(); index++) {
1357  k.SetValue(index, knots[index -1]);
1358  m.SetValue(index, multiplicities[index -1]);
1359  }
1360 
1361  this->myCurve = new Geom_BSplineCurve (p, w, k, m, degree, periodic?Standard_True:Standard_False, checkrational?Standard_True:Standard_False);
1362 
1363 }

1427 
1428 void GeomBSplineCurve::workAroundOCCTBug(const std::vector<double>& weights)
1429 {
1430  // If during assignment of weights (during the for loop below) all weights
1431  // become (temporarily) equal even though weights does not have equal values
1432  // OCCT will convert all the weights (the already assigned and those not yet assigned)
1433  // to 1.0 (nonrational b-splines have 1.0 weights). This may lead to the assignment of wrong
1434  // of weight values.
1435  //
1436  // Little hack is to set the last weight to a value different from last but one current and to-be-assigned
1437 
1438  if (weights.size() < 2) // at least two poles/weights
1439  return;
1440 
1441  auto lastindex = myCurve->NbPoles(); // OCCT is base-1
1442  auto lastbutonevalue = myCurve->Weight(lastindex-1);
1443  double fakelastvalue = lastbutonevalue + weights[weights.size()-2];
1444  myCurve->SetWeight(weights.size(),fakelastvalue);
1445 }
1446 
1447 void GeomBSplineCurve::setPoles(const std::vector<Base::Vector3d>& poles, const std::vector<double>& weights)
1448 {
1449  if (poles.size() != weights.size())
1450  throw Base::ValueError("poles and weights mismatch");
1451 
1452  workAroundOCCTBug(weights);
1453 
1454  Standard_Integer index=1;
1455 
1456  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < poles.size(); i++, index++) {
1457  setPole(index, poles[i], weights[i]);
1458  }
1459 }
1460 
1461 void GeomBSplineCurve::setPoles(const std::vector<Base::Vector3d>& poles)
1462 {
1463  Standard_Integer index=1;
1464 
1465  for (auto it = poles.begin(); it != poles.end(); ++it, index++){
1466  setPole(index, *it);
1467  }
1468 }
1469 
1470 std::vector<Base::Vector3d> GeomBSplineCurve::getPoles() const
1471 {
1472  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> poles;
1473  poles.reserve(myCurve->NbPoles());
1474  TColgp_Array1OfPnt p(1,myCurve->NbPoles());
1475  myCurve->Poles(p);
1476 
1477  for (Standard_Integer i=p.Lower(); i<=p.Upper(); i++) {
1478  const gp_Pnt& pnt = p(i);
1479  poles.emplace_back(pnt.X(), pnt.Y(), pnt.Z());
1480  }
1481  return poles;
1482 }

1484 std::vector<double> GeomBSplineCurve::getWeights() const
1485 {
1486  std::vector<double> weights;
1487  weights.reserve(myCurve->NbPoles());
1488  TColStd_Array1OfReal w(1,myCurve->NbPoles());
1489  myCurve->Weights(w);
1490 
1491  for (Standard_Integer i=w.Lower(); i<=w.Upper(); i++) {
1492  const Standard_Real& real = w(i);
1493  weights.push_back(real);
1494  }
1495  return weights;
1496 }

1618 void GeomBSplineCurve::interpolate(const std::vector<gp_Pnt>& p, Standard_Boolean periodic)
1619 {
1620  if (p.size() < 2)
1621  Standard_ConstructionError::Raise();
1622 
1623  double tol3d = Precision::Approximation();
1624  Handle(TColgp_HArray1OfPnt) pts = new TColgp_HArray1OfPnt(1, p.size());
1625  for (std::size_t i=0; i<p.size(); i++) {
1626  pts->SetValue(i+1, p[i]);
1627  }
1628 
1629  GeomAPI_Interpolate interpolate(pts, periodic, tol3d);
1630  interpolate.Perform();
1631  this->myCurve = interpolate.Curve();
1632 }
1633 
1634 void GeomBSplineCurve::interpolate(const std::vector<gp_Pnt>& p,
1635  const std::vector<gp_Vec>& t)
1636 {
1637  if (p.size() < 2)
1638  Standard_ConstructionError::Raise();
1639  if (p.size() != t.size())
1640  Standard_ConstructionError::Raise();
1641 
1642  double tol3d = Precision::Approximation();
1643  Handle(TColgp_HArray1OfPnt) pts = new TColgp_HArray1OfPnt(1, p.size());
1644  for (std::size_t i=0; i<p.size(); i++) {
1645  pts->SetValue(i+1, p[i]);
1646  }
1647 
1648  TColgp_Array1OfVec tgs(1, t.size());
1649  Handle(TColStd_HArray1OfBoolean) fgs = new TColStd_HArray1OfBoolean(1, t.size());
1650  for (std::size_t i=0; i<p.size(); i++) {
1651  tgs.SetValue(i+1, t[i]);
1652  fgs->SetValue(i+1, Standard_True);
1653  }
1654 
1655  GeomAPI_Interpolate interpolate(pts, Standard_False, tol3d);
1656  interpolate.Load(tgs, fgs);
1657  interpolate.Perform();
1658  this->myCurve = interpolate.Curve();
1659 }
1660 
1661 void GeomBSplineCurve::getCardinalSplineTangents(const std::vector<gp_Pnt>& p,
1662  const std::vector<double>& c,
1663  std::vector<gp_Vec>& t) const
1664 {
1665  // https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kubisch_Hermitescher_Spline#Cardinal_Spline
1666  if (p.size() < 2)
1667  Standard_ConstructionError::Raise();
1668  if (p.size() != c.size())
1669  Standard_ConstructionError::Raise();
1670 
1671  t.resize(p.size());
1672  if (p.size() == 2) {
1673  t[0] = gp_Vec(p[0], p[1]);
1674  t[1] = gp_Vec(p[0], p[1]);
1675  }
1676  else {
1677  std::size_t e = p.size() - 1;
1678 
1679  for (std::size_t i = 1; i < e; i++) {
1680  gp_Vec v = gp_Vec(p[i-1], p[i+1]);
1681  double f = 0.5 * (1-c[i]);
1682  v.Scale(f);
1683  t[i] = v;
1684  }
1685 
1686  t[0] = t[1];
1687  t[t.size()-1] = t[t.size()-2];
1688  }
1689 }
1690 
1691 void GeomBSplineCurve::getCardinalSplineTangents(const std::vector<gp_Pnt>& p, double c,
1692  std::vector<gp_Vec>& t) const
1693 {
1694  // https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kubisch_Hermitescher_Spline#Cardinal_Spline
1695  if (p.size() < 2)
1696  Standard_ConstructionError::Raise();
1697 
1698  t.resize(p.size());
1699  if (p.size() == 2) {
1700  t[0] = gp_Vec(p[0], p[1]);
1701  t[1] = gp_Vec(p[0], p[1]);
1702  }
1703  else {
1704  std::size_t e = p.size() - 1;
1705  double f = 0.5 * (1-c);
1706 
1707  for (std::size_t i = 1; i < e; i++) {
1708  gp_Vec v = gp_Vec(p[i-1], p[i+1]);
1709  v.Scale(f);
1710  t[i] = v;
1711  }
1712 
1713  t[0] = t[1];
1714  t[t.size()-1] = t[t.size()-2];
1715  }
1716 }

1741 void GeomBSplineCurve::approximate(double tol3d, int maxSegments, int maxDegree,
1742  GeomAbs_Shape continuity)
1743 {
1744  try {
1745  GeomAdaptor_Curve adapt(myCurve);
1746  Handle(GeomAdaptor_HCurve) hCurve = new GeomAdaptor_HCurve(adapt);
1747  Approx_Curve3d approx(hCurve, tol3d, continuity, maxSegments, maxDegree);
1748  if (approx.IsDone()) {
1749  this->setHandle(approx.Curve());
1750  }
1751  else if (approx.HasResult()) {
1752  throw Standard_Failure("Approximation of B-Spline succeeded but is outside of tolerance");
1753  }
1754  else {
1755  throw Standard_Failure("Approximation of B-Spline failed");
1756  }
1757  }
1758  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
1759  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, e.GetMessageString())
1760  }
1761 }

1763 void GeomBSplineCurve::approximate(const std::vector<Base::Vector3d>& pnts,
1764  int minDegree, int maxDegree,
1765  GeomAbs_Shape continuity, double tol3d)
1766 {
1767  try {
1768  TColgp_Array1OfPnt coords(1, static_cast<int>(pnts.size()));
1769  Standard_Integer index = 1;
1770  for (const auto& it : pnts) {
1771  coords(index++) = gp_Pnt(it.x, it.y, it.z);
1772  }
1773 
1774  GeomAPI_PointsToBSpline fit(coords, minDegree, maxDegree, continuity, tol3d);
1775  const Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve)& spline = fit.Curve();
1776  if (!spline.IsNull()) {
1777  setHandle(spline);
1778  }
1779  else {
1780  throw Standard_Failure("Failed to approximate B-Spline");
1781  }
1782  }
1783  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
1784  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, e.GetMessageString())
1785  }
1786 }

1874 bool GeomBSplineCurve::removeKnot(int index, int multiplicity, double tolerance)
1875 {
1876  try {
1877  Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve) curve =Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve)::DownCast(myCurve->Copy());
1878  if (curve->RemoveKnot(index, multiplicity, tolerance)) {
1879 
1880  // It can happen that OCCT computes a negative weight but still claims the removal was successful
1881  TColStd_Array1OfReal weights(1, curve->NbPoles());
1882  curve->Weights(weights);
1883  for (Standard_Integer i = weights.Lower(); i <= weights.Upper(); i++) {
1884  double v = weights(i);
1885  if (v <= gp::Resolution())
1886  return false;
1887  }
1888 
1889  myCurve = curve;
1890  return true;
1891  }
1892 
1893  return false;
1894  }
1895  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
1896  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
1897  }
1898 }
1899 
1900 void GeomBSplineCurve::Trim(double u, double v)
1901 {
1902  auto splitUnwrappedBSpline = [this](double u, double v) {
1903  // it makes a copy internally (checked in the source code of OCCT)
1904  auto handle = GeomConvert::SplitBSplineCurve ( myCurve,
1905  u,
1906  v,
1907  Precision::Confusion()
1908  );
1909  setHandle(handle);
1910  };
1911 
1912  try {
1913  if (isPeriodic() && (v < u)) {
1914  v = v + (getLastParameter() - getFirstParameter()); // v needs one extra lap
1915  }
1916  splitUnwrappedBSpline(u, v);
1917  }
1918  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
1919  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
1920  }
1921 }
1922 
1923 void GeomBSplineCurve::scaleKnotsToBounds(double u0, double u1)
1924 {
1925  try {
1926  Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve) curve = Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve)::DownCast(myCurve->Copy());
1927  Standard_RangeError_Raise_if (u1 <= u0, " ");
1928  TColStd_Array1OfReal k(1,curve->NbKnots());
1929  curve->Knots(k);
1930  if ((abs(u0-k.First()) > Precision::Confusion()) || (abs(u1-k.Last()) > Precision::Confusion())) {
1931  BSplCLib::Reparametrize(u0, u1, k);
1932  curve->SetKnots(k);
1933  }
1934  myCurve = curve;
1935  return;
1936  }
1937  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
1938  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
1939  }
1940 }

1947 
1948 void GeomBSplineCurve::Save(Base::Writer& writer) const
1949 {
1950  // save the attributes of the father class
1951  GeomCurve::Save(writer);
1952 
1953  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> poles = this->getPoles();
1954  std::vector<double> weights = this->getWeights();
1955  std::vector<double> knots = this->getKnots();
1956  std::vector<int> mults = this->getMultiplicities();
1957  int degree = this->getDegree();
1958  bool isperiodic = this->isPeriodic();
1959 
1960  writer.Stream()
1961  << writer.ind()
1962  << "<BSplineCurve "
1963  << "PolesCount=\"" << poles.size() <<
1964  "\" KnotsCount=\"" << knots.size() <<
1965  "\" Degree=\"" << degree <<
1966  "\" IsPeriodic=\"" << (int) isperiodic <<
1967  "\">" << std::endl;
1968 
1969  writer.incInd();
1970 
1971  std::vector<Base::Vector3d>::const_iterator itp;
1972  std::vector<double>::const_iterator itw;
1973 
1974  for (itp = poles.begin(), itw = weights.begin(); itp != poles.end() && itw != weights.end(); ++itp, ++itw) {
1975  writer.Stream()
1976  << writer.ind()
1977  << "<Pole "
1978  << "X=\"" << (*itp).x <<
1979  "\" Y=\"" << (*itp).y <<
1980  "\" Z=\"" << (*itp).z <<
1981  "\" Weight=\"" << (*itw) <<
1982  "\"/>" << std::endl;
1983  }
1984 
1985  std::vector<double>::const_iterator itk;
1986  std::vector<int>::const_iterator itm;
1987 
1988  for (itk = knots.begin(), itm = mults.begin(); itk != knots.end() && itm != mults.end(); ++itk, ++itm) {
1989  writer.Stream()
1990  << writer.ind()
1991  << "<Knot "
1992  << "Value=\"" << (*itk)
1993  << "\" Mult=\"" << (*itm) <<
1994  "\"/>" << std::endl;
1995  }
1996 
1997  writer.decInd();
1998  writer.Stream() << writer.ind() << "</BSplineCurve>" << std::endl ;
1999 }
2000 
2001 void GeomBSplineCurve::Restore(Base::XMLReader& reader)
2002 {
2003  // read the attributes of the father class
2004  GeomCurve::Restore(reader);
2005 
2006  reader.readElement("BSplineCurve");
2007  // get the value of my attribute
2008  int polescount = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("PolesCount");
2009  int knotscount = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("KnotsCount");
2010  int degree = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("Degree");
2011  bool isperiodic = (bool) reader.getAttributeAsInteger("IsPeriodic");
2012 
2013  // Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve) spline = new
2014  // Geom_BSplineCurve(occpoles,occweights,occknots,occmults,degree,
2015  // Base::asBoolean(periodic),
2016  // Base::asBoolean(CheckRational));
2017 
2018  TColgp_Array1OfPnt p(1,polescount);
2019  TColStd_Array1OfReal w(1,polescount);
2020  TColStd_Array1OfReal k(1,knotscount);
2021  TColStd_Array1OfInteger m(1,knotscount);
2022 
2023  for (int i = 1; i <= polescount; i++) {
2024  reader.readElement("Pole");
2025  double X = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("X");
2026  double Y = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("Y");
2027  double Z = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("Z");
2028  double W = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("Weight");
2029  p.SetValue(i, gp_Pnt(X,Y,Z));
2030  w.SetValue(i, W);
2031  }
2032 
2033  for (int i = 1; i <= knotscount; i++) {
2034  reader.readElement("Knot");
2035  double val = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("Value");
2036  Standard_Integer mult = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("Mult");
2037  k.SetValue(i, val);
2038  m.SetValue(i, mult);
2039  }
2040 
2041  reader.readEndElement("BSplineCurve");
2042  // Geom_BSplineCurve(occpoles,occweights,occknots,occmults,degree,periodic,CheckRational
2043 
2044  try {
2045  Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve) spline = new Geom_BSplineCurve(p, w, k, m, degree, isperiodic ? Standard_True : Standard_False, Standard_False);
2046 
2047  if (!spline.IsNull())
2048  this->myCurve = spline;
2049  else
2050  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,"BSpline restore failed")
2051  }
2052  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
2053 
2054  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
2055  }
2056 }
2057

2060 {
2061  return new BSplineCurvePy(dynamic_cast<GeomBSplineCurve*>(this->clone()));
2062 }
2063 
2064 bool GeomBSplineCurve::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
2065 {
2066  if(_other.getTypeId() != getTypeId()) {
2067  if (isLinear() && _other.isDerivedFrom(GeomCurve::getClassTypeId())) {
2068  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> geo(toLineSegment());
2069  if (geo)
2070  return geo->isSame(_other, tol, atol);
2071  }
2072  return false;
2073  }
2074 
2075  auto &other = dynamic_cast<const GeomBSplineCurve &>(_other);
2076  (void)atol;
2077 
2078  if(countPoles() != other.countPoles()
2079  || countKnots() != other.countKnots()
2080  || getDegree() != other.getDegree()
2081  || isPeriodic() != other.isPeriodic())
2082  return false;
2083 
2084  double tol2 = tol*tol;
2085  for(int i=1, c=countPoles(); i<=c; ++i) {
2086  if(myCurve->Pole(i).SquareDistance(other.myCurve->Pole(i)) > tol2
2087  || fabs(myCurve->Weight(i) - other.myCurve->Weight(i)) > tol)
2088  return false;
2089  }
2090 
2091 
2092  for(int i=1, c=countKnots(); i<=c; ++i) {
2093  if(fabs(myCurve->Knot(i) - other.myCurve->Knot(i)) > tol)
2094  return false;
2095  }
2096  return true;
2097 }

2236 GeomBSplineCurve* GeomConic::toNurbs(double first, double last) const
2237 {
2238  Handle(Geom_Conic) conic = Handle(Geom_Conic)::DownCast(handle());
2239  Handle(Geom_Curve) curve = new Geom_TrimmedCurve(conic, first, last);
2240 
2241  // pass the trimmed conic
2242  Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve) bspline = GeomConvert::CurveToBSplineCurve(curve);
2243  Standard_Real fnew = bspline->FirstParameter(), lnew = bspline->LastParameter(), UTol;
2244  if (!bspline->IsPeriodic()) {
2245  bspline->Resolution(Precision::Confusion(), UTol);
2246  if (Abs(first - fnew) > UTol || Abs(last - lnew) > UTol) {
2247  TColStd_Array1OfReal knots(1,bspline->NbKnots());
2248  bspline->Knots(knots);
2249  BSplCLib::Reparametrize(first, last, knots);
2250  bspline->SetKnots(knots);
2251  }
2252  }
2253 
2254  return new GeomBSplineCurve(bspline);
2255 }
2256 
2257 bool GeomConic::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
2258 {
2259  if(!_other.isDerivedFrom(GeomConic::getClassTypeId()))
2260  return false;
2261 
2262  auto &other = static_cast<const GeomConic &>(_other);
2263 
2264  Handle(Geom_Conic) conic = Handle(Geom_Conic)::DownCast(handle());
2265  Handle(Geom_Conic) conic2 = Handle(Geom_Conic)::DownCast(other.handle());
2266 
2267  return conic->Position().XDirection().Angle(conic2->Position().XDirection()) <= atol
2268  && conic->Position().YDirection().Angle(conic2->Position().YDirection()) <= atol
2269  && Base::DistanceP2(getLocation(),other.getLocation()) <= tol*tol;
2270 }

2330 
2331 bool GeomTrimmedCurve::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
2332 {
2333  if(_other.getTypeId() != getTypeId())
2334  return false;
2335 
2336  auto &other = static_cast<const GeomTrimmedCurve &>(_other);
2337  double u,v,u1,v1;
2338  getRange(u,v);
2339  other.getRange(u1,v1);
2340  if(fabs(u-u1)>tol || fabs(v-v1)>tol)
2341  return false;
2342 
2343  Handle(Geom_Curve) basis = myCurve->BasisCurve();
2344  Handle(Geom_Curve) basis1 = other.myCurve->BasisCurve();
2345  if(basis.IsNull() || basis1.IsNull() || basis->DynamicType() != basis1->DynamicType())
2346  return false;
2347 
2348  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> b(makeFromCurve(basis));
2349  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> b1(makeFromCurve(basis1));
2350  if (b && b1 && b->isSame(*b1, tol, atol))
2351  return true;
2352  return false;
2353 }

2355 bool GeomTrimmedCurve::intersectBasisCurves( const GeomTrimmedCurve * c,
2356  std::vector<std::pair<Base::Vector3d, Base::Vector3d>>& points,
2357  double tol) const
2358 {
2359  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) curve1 = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast(handle());
2360  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) curve2 = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast(c->handle());
2361 
2362  Handle(Geom_Curve) bcurve1 = curve1->BasisCurve();
2363  Handle(Geom_Curve) bcurve2 = curve2->BasisCurve();
2364 
2365 
2366  if(!bcurve1.IsNull() && !bcurve2.IsNull()) {
2367 
2368  return intersect(bcurve1, bcurve2, points, tol);
2369  }
2370  else
2371  return false;
2372 
2373 }

2580  assert(!c.IsNull());
2581 
2582  if (newdir.Sqr() < Precision::SquareConfusion())
2583  return;//zero vector was passed. Keep the old orientation.
2584 
2585  try {
2586  gp_Ax2 pos = c->Position();
2587  //OCC should keep the old main Direction (Z), and change YDirection to accommodate the new XDirection.
2588  pos.SetXDirection(gp_Dir(newdir.x, newdir.y, newdir.z));
2589  c->SetPosition(pos);
2590  }
2591  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
2592 
2593  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
2594  }
2595 }

2640 GeomBSplineCurve* GeomCircle::toNurbs(double first, double last) const
2641 {
2642  // for an arc of circle use the generic method
2643  if (first != 0 || last != 2*M_PI) {
2644  return GeomConic::toNurbs(first, last);
2645  }
2646 
2647  Handle(Geom_Circle) conic = Handle(Geom_Circle)::DownCast(handle());
2648  double radius = conic->Radius();
2649 
2650  TColgp_Array1OfPnt poles(1, 7);
2651  poles(1) = gp_Pnt(radius, 0, 0);
2652  poles(2) = gp_Pnt(radius, 2*radius, 0);
2653  poles(3) = gp_Pnt(-radius, 2*radius, 0);
2654  poles(4) = gp_Pnt(-radius, 0, 0);
2655  poles(5) = gp_Pnt(-radius, -2*radius, 0);
2656  poles(6) = gp_Pnt(radius, -2*radius, 0);
2657  poles(7) = gp_Pnt(radius, 0, 0);
2658 
2659  gp_Trsf trsf;
2660  trsf.SetTransformation(conic->Position(), gp_Ax3());
2661  TColStd_Array1OfReal weights(1,7);
2662  for (int i=1; i<=7; i++) {
2663  poles(i).Transform(trsf);
2664  weights(i) = 1;
2665  }
2666  weights(1) = 3;
2667  weights(4) = 3;
2668  weights(7) = 3;
2669 
2670  TColStd_Array1OfInteger mults(1, 3);
2671  mults(1) = 4;
2672  mults(2) = 3;
2673  mults(3) = 4;
2674 
2675  TColStd_Array1OfReal knots(1, 3);
2676  knots(1) = 0;
2677  knots(2) = M_PI;
2678  knots(3) = 2*M_PI;
2679 
2680  Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve) spline = new Geom_BSplineCurve(poles, weights,knots, mults, 3,
2681  Standard_False, Standard_True);
2682  return new GeomBSplineCurve(spline);
2683 }

2712 void GeomCircle::Save(Base::Writer& writer) const
2713 {
2714  // save the attributes of the father class
2715  GeomCurve::Save(writer);
2716 
2717  gp_Pnt center = this->myCurve->Axis().Location();
2718  gp_Dir normal = this->myCurve->Axis().Direction();
2719  gp_Dir xdir = this->myCurve->XAxis().Direction();
2720 
2721  gp_Ax2 xdirref(center, normal); // this is a reference XY for the circle
2722  double AngleXU = -xdir.AngleWithRef(xdirref.XDirection(),normal);
2723

2725  << writer.ind()
2726  << "<Circle "
2727  << "CenterX=\"" << center.X() <<
2728  "\" CenterY=\"" << center.Y() <<
2729  "\" CenterZ=\"" << center.Z() <<
2730  "\" NormalX=\"" << normal.X() <<
2731  "\" NormalY=\"" << normal.Y() <<
2732  "\" NormalZ=\"" << normal.Z() <<
2733  "\" AngleXU=\"" << AngleXU <<
2734  "\" Radius=\"" << this->myCurve->Radius() <<
2735  "\"/>" << std::endl;

2738 void GeomCircle::Restore(Base::XMLReader& reader)
2739 {
2740  // read the attributes of the father class
2741  GeomCurve::Restore(reader);
2742 
2743  double CenterX,CenterY,CenterZ,NormalX,NormalY,NormalZ,Radius;
2744  double AngleXU=0;
2745  // read my Element
2746  reader.readElement("Circle");
2747  // get the value of my Attribute
2748  CenterX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterX");
2749  CenterY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterY");
2750  CenterZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterZ");
2751  NormalX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalX");
2752  NormalY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalY");
2753  NormalZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalZ");
2754  if (reader.hasAttribute("AngleXU"))
2755  AngleXU = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("AngleXU");
2756  Radius = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("Radius");
2757 
2758  // set the read geometry
2759  gp_Pnt p1(CenterX,CenterY,CenterZ);
2760  gp_Dir norm(NormalX,NormalY,NormalZ);
2761 
2762  gp_Ax1 normaxis(p1,norm);
2763  gp_Ax2 xdir(p1, norm);
2764  xdir.Rotate(normaxis,AngleXU);
2765 
2766  try {
2767  GC_MakeCircle mc(xdir, Radius);
2768  if (!mc.IsDone())
2769  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,gce_ErrorStatusText(mc.Status()))
2770 
2771  this->myCurve = mc.Value();
2772  }
2773  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
2774 
2775  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
2776  }
2777 }

2784 bool GeomCircle::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
2785 {

2787  return false;
2788 
2789  (void)atol;
2790  auto &other = static_cast<const GeomCircle &>(_other);
2791  return GeomConic::isSame(other,tol,atol) && fabs(getRadius() - other.getRadius()) <= tol;
2792 }

2871 double GeomArcOfCircle::getAngle(bool emulateCCWXY) const

2878 
2888 void GeomArcOfCircle::getRange(double& u, double& v, bool emulateCCWXY) const
2889 {
2890  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) curve = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast(handle());
2891  u = curve->FirstParameter();
2892  v = curve->LastParameter();
2893  if (emulateCCWXY){
2894  Handle(Geom_Conic) conic = Handle(Geom_Conic)::DownCast(curve->BasisCurve());
2895  double angleXU = -conic->Position().XDirection().AngleWithRef(gp_Dir(1.0,0.0,0.0), gp_Dir(0.0,0.0,1.0));
2896  double u1 = u, v1 = v;//the true arc curve parameters, cached. u,v will contain the rotation-corrected and swapped angles.
2897  if (conic->Axis().Direction().Z() > 0.0){
2898  //normal CCW arc
2899  u = u1 + angleXU;
2900  v = v1 + angleXU;
2901  }
2902  else {
2903  //reversed (CW) arc
2904  u = angleXU - v1;
2905  v = angleXU - u1;
2906  }
2907 
2908  if (v < u)
2909  v += 2*M_PI;
2910  if (v-u > 2*M_PI)
2911  v -= 2*M_PI;
2912  }
2913 }
2914 
2924 void GeomArcOfCircle::setRange(double u, double v, bool emulateCCWXY)
2925 {
2926  try {
2927  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) curve = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast(handle());
2928  if (emulateCCWXY){
2929  Handle(Geom_Conic) conic = Handle(Geom_Conic)::DownCast(curve->BasisCurve());
2930  double angleXU = -conic->Position().XDirection().AngleWithRef(gp_Dir(1.0,0.0,0.0), gp_Dir(0.0,0.0,1.0));
2931  double u1 = u, v1 = v;//the values that were passed, ccw angles from X axis. u,v will contain the rotation-corrected and swapped angles.
2932  if (conic->Axis().Direction().Z() > 0.0){
2933  //normal CCW arc
2934  u = u1 - angleXU;
2935  v = v1 - angleXU;
2936  }
2937  else {
2938  //reversed (CW) arc
2939  u = angleXU - v1;
2940  v = angleXU - u1;
2941  }
2942  }
2943 
2944  curve->SetTrim(u, v);
2945  }
2946  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
2947 
2948  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
2949  }
2950 }

2988 void GeomArcOfCircle::Restore(Base::XMLReader &reader)
2989 {
2990  // read the attributes of the father class
2991  Geometry::Restore(reader);
2992 
2993  double CenterX,CenterY,CenterZ,NormalX,NormalY,NormalZ,Radius,StartAngle,EndAngle;
2994  double AngleXU=0;
2995  // read my Element
2996  reader.readElement("ArcOfCircle");
2997  // get the value of my Attribute
2998  CenterX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterX");
2999  CenterY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterY");
3000  CenterZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterZ");
3001  NormalX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalX");
3002  NormalY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalY");
3003  NormalZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalZ");
3004  if (reader.hasAttribute("AngleXU"))
3005  AngleXU = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("AngleXU");
3006  Radius = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("Radius");
3007  StartAngle = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("StartAngle");
3008  EndAngle = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("EndAngle");

3012  gp_Dir norm(NormalX,NormalY,NormalZ);

3020  if (!mc.IsDone())

3022  GC_MakeArcOfCircle ma(mc.Value()->Circ(), StartAngle, EndAngle, Standard_True);
3023  if (!ma.IsDone())

3029

3031  this->myCurve->SetTrim(tmpcurve->FirstParameter(), tmpcurve->LastParameter());
3032  }
3033  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {

3086 GeomBSplineCurve* GeomEllipse::toNurbs(double first, double last) const
3087 {

3090  return GeomConic::toNurbs(first, last);
3091  }

3094  Standard_Real majorRadius = conic->MajorRadius();
3095  Standard_Real minorRadius = conic->MinorRadius();
3096

3098  poles(1) = gp_Pnt(majorRadius, 0, 0);
3099  poles(2) = gp_Pnt(majorRadius, 2*minorRadius, 0);
3100  poles(3) = gp_Pnt(-majorRadius, 2*minorRadius, 0);
3101  poles(4) = gp_Pnt(-majorRadius, 0, 0);
3102  poles(5) = gp_Pnt(-majorRadius, -2*minorRadius, 0);
3103  poles(6) = gp_Pnt(majorRadius, -2*minorRadius, 0);
3104  poles(7) = gp_Pnt(majorRadius, 0, 0);
3105 
3106  gp_Trsf trsf;
3107  trsf.SetTransformation(conic->Position(), gp_Ax3());
3108  TColStd_Array1OfReal weights(1,7);
3109  for (int i=1; i<=7; i++) {
3110  poles(i).Transform(trsf);
3111  weights(i) = 1;
3112  }
3113  weights(1) = 3;
3114  weights(4) = 3;
3115  weights(7) = 3;
3116 
3117  TColStd_Array1OfInteger mults(1, 3);
3118  mults(1) = 4;
3119  mults(2) = 3;
3120  mults(3) = 4;
3121 
3122  TColStd_Array1OfReal knots(1, 3);
3123  knots(1) = 0;
3124  knots(2) = 1;
3125  knots(3) = 2;
3126 
3127  Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve) spline = new Geom_BSplineCurve(poles, weights,knots, mults, 3,

3221 void GeomEllipse::Save(Base::Writer& writer) const
3222 {
3223  // save the attributes of the father class
3224  GeomCurve::Save(writer);
3225 
3226  gp_Pnt center = this->myCurve->Axis().Location();
3227  gp_Dir normal = this->myCurve->Axis().Direction();
3228  gp_Dir xdir = this->myCurve->XAxis().Direction();
3229 
3230  gp_Ax2 xdirref(center, normal); // this is a reference XY for the ellipse
3231 
3232  double AngleXU = -xdir.AngleWithRef(xdirref.XDirection(),normal);
3233 
3234 
3235  writer.Stream()
3236  << writer.ind()
3237  << "<Ellipse "
3238  << "CenterX=\"" << center.X() << "\" "
3239  << "CenterY=\"" << center.Y() << "\" "
3240  << "CenterZ=\"" << center.Z() << "\" "
3241  << "NormalX=\"" << normal.X() << "\" "
3242  << "NormalY=\"" << normal.Y() << "\" "
3243  << "NormalZ=\"" << normal.Z() << "\" "
3244  << "MajorRadius=\"" << this->myCurve->MajorRadius() << "\" "
3245  << "MinorRadius=\"" << this->myCurve->MinorRadius() << "\" "
3246  << "AngleXU=\"" << AngleXU << "\" "
3247  << "/>" << std::endl;
3248 }

3250 void GeomEllipse::Restore(Base::XMLReader& reader)
3251 {
3252  // read the attributes of the father class
3253  GeomCurve::Restore(reader);
3254 
3255  double CenterX,CenterY,CenterZ,NormalX,NormalY,NormalZ,MajorRadius,MinorRadius,AngleXU;
3256  // read my Element
3257  reader.readElement("Ellipse");
3258  // get the value of my Attribute
3259  CenterX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterX");
3260  CenterY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterY");
3261  CenterZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterZ");
3262  NormalX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalX");
3263  NormalY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalY");
3264  NormalZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalZ");
3265  MajorRadius = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("MajorRadius");
3266  MinorRadius = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("MinorRadius");
3267 
3268  // This is for backwards compatibility
3269  if(reader.hasAttribute("AngleXU"))
3270  AngleXU = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("AngleXU");
3271  else
3272  AngleXU = 0;
3273 
3274  // set the read geometry
3275  gp_Pnt p1(CenterX,CenterY,CenterZ);
3276  gp_Dir norm(NormalX,NormalY,NormalZ);
3277 
3278  gp_Ax1 normaxis(p1,norm);
3279 
3280  gp_Ax2 xdir(p1, norm);
3281 
3282  xdir.Rotate(normaxis,AngleXU);
3283 
3284  try {
3285  GC_MakeEllipse mc(xdir, MajorRadius, MinorRadius);
3286  if (!mc.IsDone())
3287  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,gce_ErrorStatusText(mc.Status()))
3288 
3289  this->myCurve = mc.Value();
3290  }
3291  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
3292 
3293  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
3294  }
3295 }

3302 bool GeomEllipse::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
3303 {
3304  if(_other.getTypeId() != getTypeId())
3305  return false;
3306 
3307  (void)atol;
3308  auto &other = static_cast<const GeomEllipse &>(_other);
3309  return GeomConic::isSame(other,tol,atol)
3310  && fabs(getMajorRadius() - other.getMajorRadius()) <= tol
3311  && fabs(getMinorRadius() - other.getMinorRadius()) <= tol;
3312 }

3435 void GeomArcOfEllipse::setMajorAxisDir(Base::Vector3d newdir)
3436 {
3437  Handle(Geom_Ellipse) c = Handle(Geom_Ellipse)::DownCast( myCurve->BasisCurve() );
3438  assert(!c.IsNull());
3439  if (newdir.Sqr() < Precision::SquareConfusion())
3440  return;//zero vector was passed. Keep the old orientation.
3441  try {
3442  gp_Ax2 pos = c->Position();
3443  pos.SetXDirection(gp_Dir(newdir.x, newdir.y, newdir.z));//OCC should keep the old main Direction (Z), and change YDirection to accommodate the new XDirection.
3444  c->SetPosition(pos);
3445  }
3446  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
3447 
3448  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
3449  }
3450 }
3451 
3459 void GeomArcOfEllipse::getRange(double& u, double& v, bool emulateCCWXY) const
3460 {
3461  u = myCurve->FirstParameter();
3462  v = myCurve->LastParameter();
3463  if (emulateCCWXY) {
3464  if (isReversed()) {
3465  std::swap(u,v);
3466  u = -u; v = -v;
3467  if (v < u)
3468  v += 2*M_PI;
3469  if (v-u > 2*M_PI)
3470  v -= 2*M_PI;
3471  }
3472  }
3473 }
3474 
3482 void GeomArcOfEllipse::setRange(double u, double v, bool emulateCCWXY)
3483 {
3484  try {
3485  if (emulateCCWXY) {
3486  if (isReversed()) {
3487  std::swap(u,v);
3488  u = -u; v = -v;
3489  }
3490  }
3491  myCurve->SetTrim(u, v);
3492  }
3493  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
3494 
3495  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
3496  }
3497 }

3538 void GeomArcOfEllipse::Restore(Base::XMLReader &reader)
3539 {
3540  // read the attributes of the father class
3541  GeomCurve::Restore(reader);
3542 
3543  double CenterX,CenterY,CenterZ,NormalX,NormalY,NormalZ,MajorRadius,MinorRadius,AngleXU,StartAngle,EndAngle;
3544  // read my Element
3545  reader.readElement("ArcOfEllipse");
3546  // get the value of my Attribute
3547  CenterX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterX");
3548  CenterY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterY");
3549  CenterZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterZ");
3550  NormalX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalX");
3551  NormalY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalY");
3552  NormalZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalZ");
3553  MajorRadius = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("MajorRadius");
3554  MinorRadius = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("MinorRadius");
3555  AngleXU = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("AngleXU");
3556  StartAngle = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("StartAngle");
3557  EndAngle = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("EndAngle");
3558 
3559 
3560  // set the read geometry
3561  gp_Pnt p1(CenterX,CenterY,CenterZ);
3562  gp_Dir norm(NormalX,NormalY,NormalZ);
3563 
3564  gp_Ax1 normaxis(p1,norm);
3565 
3566  gp_Ax2 xdir(p1, norm);
3567 
3568  xdir.Rotate(normaxis,AngleXU);
3569 
3570  try {
3571  GC_MakeEllipse mc(xdir, MajorRadius, MinorRadius);
3572  if (!mc.IsDone())
3573  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,gce_ErrorStatusText(mc.Status()))
3574 
3575  GC_MakeArcOfEllipse ma(mc.Value()->Elips(), StartAngle, EndAngle, Standard_True);
3576  if (!ma.IsDone())
3577  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,gce_ErrorStatusText(ma.Status()))
3578 
3579  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) tmpcurve = ma.Value();
3580  Handle(Geom_Ellipse) tmpellipse = Handle(Geom_Ellipse)::DownCast(tmpcurve->BasisCurve());
3581  Handle(Geom_Ellipse) ellipse = Handle(Geom_Ellipse)::DownCast(this->myCurve->BasisCurve());
3582 
3583  ellipse->SetElips(tmpellipse->Elips());
3584  this->myCurve->SetTrim(tmpcurve->FirstParameter(), tmpcurve->LastParameter());
3585  }
3586  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
3587 
3588  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
3589  }
3590 }

3898 void GeomArcOfHyperbola::setMajorAxisDir(Base::Vector3d newdir)
3899 {
3900  Handle(Geom_Hyperbola) c = Handle(Geom_Hyperbola)::DownCast( myCurve->BasisCurve() );
3901  assert(!c.IsNull());
3902  if (newdir.Sqr() < Precision::SquareConfusion())
3903  return;//zero vector was passed. Keep the old orientation.
3904 
3905  try {
3906  gp_Ax2 pos = c->Position();
3907  pos.SetXDirection(gp_Dir(newdir.x, newdir.y, newdir.z));//OCC should keep the old main Direction (Z), and change YDirection to accommodate the new XDirection.
3908  c->SetPosition(pos);
3909  }
3910  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
3911 
3912  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
3913  }
3914 }
3915 
3916 void GeomArcOfHyperbola::getRange(double& u, double& v, bool emulateCCWXY) const
3917 {
3918  try {
3919  if (emulateCCWXY){
3920  if (isReversed()) {
3921  Handle(Geom_Hyperbola) c = Handle(Geom_Hyperbola)::DownCast(myCurve->BasisCurve());
3922  assert(!c.IsNull());
3923  c->Reverse();
3924  }
3925  }
3926  }
3927  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
3928 
3929  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
3930  }
3931 
3932  u = myCurve->FirstParameter();
3933  v = myCurve->LastParameter();
3934 }
3935 
3936 void GeomArcOfHyperbola::setRange(double u, double v, bool emulateCCWXY)
3937 {
3938  try {
3939  myCurve->SetTrim(u, v);
3940 
3941  if (emulateCCWXY) {
3942  if (isReversed()) {
3943  Handle(Geom_Hyperbola) c = Handle(Geom_Hyperbola)::DownCast(myCurve->BasisCurve());
3944  assert(!c.IsNull());
3945  c->Reverse();
3946  }
3947  }
3948  }
3949  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
3950 
3951  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
3952  }
3953 }

3961 void GeomArcOfHyperbola::Save(Base::Writer &writer) const
3962 {
3963  // save the attributes of the father class
3964  GeomCurve::Save(writer);
3965 
3966  Handle(Geom_Hyperbola) h = Handle(Geom_Hyperbola)::DownCast(this->myCurve->BasisCurve());
3967 
3968  gp_Pnt center = h->Axis().Location();
3969  gp_Dir normal = h->Axis().Direction();
3970  gp_Dir xdir = h->XAxis().Direction();
3971 
3972  gp_Ax2 xdirref(center, normal); // this is a reference XY for the ellipse
3973 
3974  double AngleXU = -xdir.AngleWithRef(xdirref.XDirection(),normal);
3975 
3976  writer.Stream()
3977  << writer.ind()
3978  << "<ArcOfHyperbola "
3979  << "CenterX=\"" << center.X() << "\" "
3980  << "CenterY=\"" << center.Y() << "\" "
3981  << "CenterZ=\"" << center.Z() << "\" "
3982  << "NormalX=\"" << normal.X() << "\" "
3983  << "NormalY=\"" << normal.Y() << "\" "
3984  << "NormalZ=\"" << normal.Z() << "\" "
3985  << "MajorRadius=\"" << h->MajorRadius() << "\" "
3986  << "MinorRadius=\"" << h->MinorRadius() << "\" "
3987  << "AngleXU=\"" << AngleXU << "\" "
3988  << "StartAngle=\"" << this->myCurve->FirstParameter() << "\" "
3989  << "EndAngle=\"" << this->myCurve->LastParameter() << "\" "
3990  << "/>" << std::endl;
3991 }
3992 
3993 void GeomArcOfHyperbola::Restore(Base::XMLReader &reader)
3994 {
3995  // read the attributes of the father class
3996  GeomCurve::Restore(reader);
3997 
3998  double CenterX,CenterY,CenterZ,NormalX,NormalY,NormalZ,MajorRadius,MinorRadius,AngleXU,StartAngle,EndAngle;
3999  // read my Element
4000  reader.readElement("ArcOfHyperbola");
4001  // get the value of my Attribute
4002  CenterX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterX");
4003  CenterY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterY");
4004  CenterZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterZ");
4005  NormalX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalX");
4006  NormalY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalY");
4007  NormalZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalZ");
4008  MajorRadius = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("MajorRadius");
4009  MinorRadius = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("MinorRadius");
4010  AngleXU = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("AngleXU");
4011  StartAngle = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("StartAngle");
4012  EndAngle = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("EndAngle");
4013 
4014 
4015  // set the read geometry
4016  gp_Pnt p1(CenterX,CenterY,CenterZ);
4017  gp_Dir norm(NormalX,NormalY,NormalZ);
4018 
4019  gp_Ax1 normaxis(p1,norm);
4020 
4021  gp_Ax2 xdir(p1, norm);
4022 
4023  xdir.Rotate(normaxis,AngleXU);
4024 
4025  try {
4026  GC_MakeHyperbola mc(xdir, MajorRadius, MinorRadius);
4027  if (!mc.IsDone())
4028  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,gce_ErrorStatusText(mc.Status()))
4029 
4030  GC_MakeArcOfHyperbola ma(mc.Value()->Hypr(), StartAngle, EndAngle, Standard_True);
4031  if (!ma.IsDone())
4032  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,gce_ErrorStatusText(ma.Status()))
4033 
4034  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) tmpcurve = ma.Value();
4035  Handle(Geom_Hyperbola) tmphyperbola = Handle(Geom_Hyperbola)::DownCast(tmpcurve->BasisCurve());
4036  Handle(Geom_Hyperbola) hyperbola = Handle(Geom_Hyperbola)::DownCast(this->myCurve->BasisCurve());
4037 
4038  hyperbola->SetHypr(tmphyperbola->Hypr());
4039  this->myCurve->SetTrim(tmpcurve->FirstParameter(), tmpcurve->LastParameter());
4040  }
4041  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
4042 
4043  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
4044  }
4045 }
4046

4049  return new ArcOfHyperbolaPy(static_cast<GeomArcOfHyperbola*>(this->clone()));
4050 }

4198 bool GeomParabola::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
4199 {
4200  if(_other.getTypeId() != getTypeId())
4201  return false;
4202 
4203  (void)atol;
4204  auto &other = static_cast<const GeomParabola &>(_other);
4205  return GeomConic::isSame(other,tol,atol) && fabs(getFocal() - other.getFocal()) < tol;
4206 }

4359 void GeomArcOfParabola::Restore(Base::XMLReader &reader)
4360 {

4362  GeomCurve::Restore(reader);
4363

4369  CenterY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterY");
4370  CenterZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("CenterZ");
4371  NormalX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalX");
4372  NormalY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalY");
4373  NormalZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("NormalZ");
4374  Focal = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("Focal");
4375  AngleXU = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("AngleXU");
4376  StartAngle = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("StartAngle");
4377  EndAngle = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("EndAngle");
4378 
4379 
4380  // set the read geometry
4381  gp_Pnt p1(CenterX,CenterY,CenterZ);
4382  gp_Dir norm(NormalX,NormalY,NormalZ);
4383 
4384  gp_Ax1 normaxis(p1,norm);
4385 
4386  gp_Ax2 xdir(p1, norm);
4387 
4388  xdir.Rotate(normaxis,AngleXU);
4389

4392  if (!mc.IsDone())

4394 
4395  GC_MakeArcOfParabola ma(mc.Value(), StartAngle, EndAngle, Standard_True);
4396  if (!ma.IsDone())

4402

4526 bool GeomLine::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
4527 {
4528  if(_other.getTypeId() != getTypeId()) {
4529  if (_other.isDerivedFrom(GeomCurve::getClassTypeId())) {
4530  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> geo(dynamic_cast<const GeomCurve&>(_other).toLine());
4531  if (geo)
4532  return isSame(*geo, tol, atol);
4533  }
4534  return false;
4535  }
4536 
4537  auto &other = dynamic_cast<const GeomLine &>(_other);
4538 
4539  return getDir().GetAngle(other.getDir()) <= atol
4540  && Base::DistanceP2(getPos(), other.getPos()) <= tol*tol;
4541 }

4601 
4602 void GeomLineSegment::setPoints(const Base::Vector3d& Start, const Base::Vector3d& End)
4603 {
4604  gp_Pnt p1(Start.x,Start.y,Start.z), p2(End.x,End.y,End.z);
4605  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) this_curv = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast(handle());
4606 
4607  try {
4608  // Create line out of two points
4609  if (p1.Distance(p2) < gp::Resolution())
4610  THROWM(Base::ValueError,"Both points are equal");
4611 
4612  GC_MakeSegment ms(p1, p2);
4613  if (!ms.IsDone()) {
4614  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,gce_ErrorStatusText(ms.Status()))
4615  }
4616 
4617  // get Geom_Line of line segment
4618  Handle(Geom_Line) this_line = Handle(Geom_Line)::DownCast
4619  (this_curv->BasisCurve());
4620  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)& that_curv =
4621  const_cast<opencascade::handle<Geom_TrimmedCurve>&>(ms.Value());
4622  Handle(Geom_Line) that_line = Handle(Geom_Line)::DownCast(that_curv->BasisCurve());
4623  this_line->SetLin(that_line->Lin());
4624  this_curv->SetTrim(that_curv->FirstParameter(), that_curv->LastParameter());
4625  }
4626  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
4627 
4628  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
4629  }
4630 }
4631

4633 unsigned int GeomLineSegment::getMemSize () const
4634 {
4635  return sizeof(Geom_TrimmedCurve) + sizeof(Geom_Line);
4636 }

4638 void GeomLineSegment::Save (Base::Writer &writer) const
4639 {
4640  // save the attributes of the father class
4641  Geometry::Save(writer);
4642 
4643  Base::Vector3d End = getEndPoint();
4644  Base::Vector3d Start = getStartPoint();
4645 
4646  writer.Stream()
4647  << writer.ind()
4648  << "<LineSegment "
4649  << "StartX=\"" << Start.x <<
4650  "\" StartY=\"" << Start.y <<
4651  "\" StartZ=\"" << Start.z <<
4652  "\" EndX=\"" << End.x <<
4653  "\" EndY=\"" << End.y <<
4654  "\" EndZ=\"" << End.z <<
4655  "\"/>" << std::endl;
4656 }
4657 
4658 void GeomLineSegment::Restore (Base::XMLReader &reader)
4659 {
4660  // read the attributes of the father class
4661  Geometry::Restore(reader);
4662 
4663  double StartX,StartY,StartZ,EndX,EndY,EndZ;
4664  // read my Element
4665  reader.readElement("LineSegment");
4666  // get the value of my Attribute
4667  StartX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("StartX");
4668  StartY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("StartY");
4669  StartZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("StartZ");
4670  EndX = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("EndX");
4671  EndY = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("EndY");
4672  EndZ = reader.getAttributeAsFloat("EndZ");
4673 
4674  Base::Vector3d start(StartX,StartY,StartZ);
4675  Base::Vector3d end(EndX,EndY,EndZ);
4676  // set the read geometry
4677  try {
4678  setPoints(start, end);
4679  }
4680  catch(Base::ValueError&) {
4681  // for a line segment construction, the only possibility of a value error is that
4682  // the points are too close. The best try to restore is incrementing the distance.
4683  // for other objects, the best effort may be just to leave default values.
4684  reader.setPartialRestore(true);
4685 
4686  if(start.x == 0) {
4687  end = start + Base::Vector3d(DBL_EPSILON,0,0);
4688  }
4689  else {
4690  end = start + Base::Vector3d(start.x*DBL_EPSILON,0,0);
4691  }
4692 
4693  setPoints(start, end);
4694  }
4695 }

4700 }

4773 bool GeomOffsetCurve::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
4774 {
4775  if(_other.getTypeId() != getTypeId())
4776  return false;
4777 
4778  auto &other = dynamic_cast<const GeomOffsetCurve &>(_other);
4779  if(myCurve->Direction().Angle(other.myCurve->Direction()) > atol || fabs(getOffset() - other.getOffset()) > tol)
4780  return false;
4781 
4782  Handle(Geom_Curve) basis = myCurve->BasisCurve();
4783  Handle(Geom_Curve) basis1 = other.myCurve->BasisCurve();
4784  if(basis.IsNull() || basis1.IsNull() || basis->DynamicType() != basis1->DynamicType())
4785  return false;
4786 
4787  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> b(makeFromCurve(basis));
4788  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> b1(makeFromCurve(basis1));
4789  return b && b1 && b->isSame(*b1, tol, atol);
4790 }

4908 double GeomSurface::curvature(double u, double v, Curvature type) const
4909 {
4910  Handle(Geom_Surface) s = Handle(Geom_Surface)::DownCast(handle());
4911  GeomLProp_SLProps prop(s,u,v,2,Precision::Confusion());
4912  if (prop.IsCurvatureDefined()) {
4913  double value = 0;
4914  switch (type) {
4915  case Maximum:
4916  value = prop.MaxCurvature();
4917  break;
4918  case Minimum:
4919  value = prop.MinCurvature();
4920  break;
4921  case Mean:
4922  value = prop.MeanCurvature();
4923  break;
4924  case Gaussian:
4925  value = prop.GaussianCurvature();
4926  break;
4927  }
4928 
4929  return value;
4930  }
4931 
4932  THROWM(Base::RuntimeError,"No curvature defined")
4933 }

4985 // Persistence implementer
4986 unsigned int GeomBezierSurface::getMemSize () const
4987 {

4989  if (!mySurface.IsNull()) {
4990  unsigned int poles = mySurface->NbUPoles();
4991  poles *= mySurface->NbVPoles();
4992  size += poles * sizeof(gp_Pnt);

4994  }
4995  return size;

5012 
5013 bool GeomBezierSurface::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
5014 {
5015  if(_other.getTypeId() != getTypeId())
5016  return false;
5017 
5018  auto &other = static_cast<const GeomBezierSurface &>(_other);
5019  Standard_Integer uc = mySurface->NbUPoles();
5020  Standard_Integer vc = mySurface->NbVPoles();
5021  if(uc != other.mySurface->NbUPoles()
5022  || vc != other.mySurface->NbVPoles()
5023  || mySurface->UDegree() != other.mySurface->UDegree()
5024  || mySurface->VDegree() != other.mySurface->VDegree())
5025  return false;
5026 
5027  (void)atol;
5028  double tol2 = tol*tol;
5029  for(Standard_Integer u=1; u<=uc; ++u) {
5030  for(Standard_Integer v=1; v<=vc; ++v) {
5031  if(mySurface->Pole(u,v).SquareDistance(other.mySurface->Pole(u,v)) > tol2
5032  || fabs(mySurface->Weight(u,v) - other.mySurface->Weight(u,v)) > tol)
5033  return false;
5034  }
5035  }
5036  return true;
5037 }

5041 TYPESYSTEM_SOURCE(Part::GeomBSplineSurface,Part::GeomSurface)
5042 
5043 GeomBSplineSurface::GeomBSplineSurface()
5044 {
5045  TColgp_Array2OfPnt poles(1,2,1,2);
5046  poles(1,1) = gp_Pnt(0.0,0.0,0.0);
5047  poles(2,1) = gp_Pnt(1.0,0.0,0.0);
5048  poles(1,2) = gp_Pnt(0.0,1.0,0.0);
5049  poles(2,2) = gp_Pnt(1.0,1.0,0.0);
5050 
5051  TColStd_Array1OfReal knots(1,2);
5052  knots(1) = 0.0;
5053  knots(2) = 1.0;
5054 
5055  TColStd_Array1OfInteger mults(1,2);
5056  mults(1) = 2;
5057  mults(2) = 2;
5058 
5059  this->mySurface = new Geom_BSplineSurface(poles, knots, knots, mults, mults, 1, 1);
5060 }
5061

5085 
5086 void GeomBSplineSurface::scaleKnotsToBounds(double u0, double u1, double v0, double v1)
5087 {
5088  try {
5089  Handle(Geom_BSplineSurface) surf = Handle(Geom_BSplineSurface)::DownCast(mySurface->Copy());
5090  Standard_RangeError_Raise_if (u1 <= u0 || v1 <= v0, " ");
5091  Standard_Real bu0,bu1,bv0,bv1;
5092  surf->Bounds(bu0,bu1,bv0,bv1);
5093  if ((abs(u0-bu0) > Precision::Confusion()) || (abs(u1-bu1) > Precision::Confusion())) {
5094  TColStd_Array1OfReal uk(1,surf->NbUKnots());
5095  surf->UKnots(uk);
5096  BSplCLib::Reparametrize(u0, u1, uk);
5097  surf->SetUKnots(uk);
5098  }
5099  if ((abs(v0-bv0) > Precision::Confusion()) || (abs(v1-bv1) > Precision::Confusion())) {
5100  TColStd_Array1OfReal vk(1,surf->NbVKnots());
5101  surf->VKnots(vk);
5102  BSplCLib::Reparametrize(v0, v1, vk);
5103  surf->SetVKnots(vk);
5104  }
5105  mySurface = surf;
5106  return;
5107  }
5108  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
5109  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,e.GetMessageString())
5110  }
5111 }
5112 
5113 // Persistence implementer
5114 unsigned int GeomBSplineSurface::getMemSize () const
5115 {
5116  unsigned int size = sizeof(Geom_BSplineSurface);
5117  if (!mySurface.IsNull()) {
5118  size += mySurface->NbUKnots() * sizeof(Standard_Real);
5119  size += mySurface->NbUKnots() * sizeof(Standard_Integer);
5120  size += mySurface->NbVKnots() * sizeof(Standard_Real);
5121  size += mySurface->NbVKnots() * sizeof(Standard_Integer);
5122  unsigned int poles = mySurface->NbUPoles();
5123  poles *= mySurface->NbVPoles();
5124  size += poles * sizeof(gp_Pnt);
5125  size += poles * sizeof(Standard_Real);
5126  }
5127  return size;
5128 }

5144 
5145 bool GeomBSplineSurface::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
5146 {
5147  if(_other.getTypeId() != getTypeId()) {
5148  if (_other.isDerivedFrom(GeomSurface::getClassTypeId()) && isPlanar()) {
5149  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> geo(toPlane());
5150  if (geo)
5151  return geo->isSame(_other, tol, atol);
5152  }
5153  return false;
5154  }
5155 
5156  auto &other = static_cast<const GeomBSplineSurface &>(_other);
5157  Standard_Integer uc = mySurface->NbUPoles();
5158  Standard_Integer vc = mySurface->NbVPoles();
5159  Standard_Integer ukc = mySurface->NbUKnots();
5160  Standard_Integer vkc = mySurface->NbVKnots();
5161  if(uc != other.mySurface->NbUPoles()
5162  || vc != other.mySurface->NbVPoles()
5163  || ukc != other.mySurface->NbUKnots()
5164  || vkc != other.mySurface->NbVKnots()
5165  || mySurface->UDegree() != other.mySurface->UDegree()
5166  || mySurface->VDegree() != other.mySurface->VDegree()
5167  || mySurface->IsUPeriodic() != other.mySurface->IsUPeriodic()
5168  || mySurface->IsVPeriodic() != other.mySurface->IsVPeriodic())
5169  return false;
5170 
5171  (void)atol;
5172  double tol2 = tol*tol;
5173  for(Standard_Integer u=1; u<=uc; ++u) {
5174  for(Standard_Integer v=1; v<=vc; ++v) {
5175  if(mySurface->Pole(u,v).SquareDistance(other.mySurface->Pole(u,v)) > tol2
5176  || fabs(mySurface->Weight(u,v) - other.mySurface->Weight(u,v)) > tol)
5177  return false;
5178  }
5179  }
5180  for(Standard_Integer u=1; u<=ukc; ++u) {
5181  if(fabs(mySurface->UKnot(u) - other.mySurface->UKnot(u)) > tol
5182  || fabs(mySurface->UMultiplicity(u) - other.mySurface->UMultiplicity(u)) > tol)
5183  return false;
5184  }
5185  for(Standard_Integer v=1; v<=ukc; ++v) {
5186  if(fabs(mySurface->VKnot(v) - other.mySurface->VKnot(v)) > tol
5187  || fabs(mySurface->VMultiplicity(v) - other.mySurface->VMultiplicity(v)) > tol)
5188  return false;
5189  }
5190  return true;
5191 }

5212 std::optional<Base::Rotation> GeomPlane::getRotation() const
5213 {
5214  Handle(Geom_ElementarySurface) s = Handle(Geom_ElementarySurface)::DownCast(handle());
5215 
5216  if (!s) {
5217  return {};
5218  }
5219 
5220  gp_Trsf trsf;
5221  trsf.SetTransformation(s->Position().Ax2(),gp_Ax3());
5222  auto q = trsf.GetRotation();
5223 
5224  return Base::Rotation(q.X(),q.Y(),q.Z(),q.W());
5225 }

5247 
5248 bool GeomElementarySurface::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
5249 {
5250  if(!_other.isDerivedFrom(GeomElementarySurface::getClassTypeId()))
5251  return false;
5252 
5253  auto &other = static_cast<const GeomElementarySurface &>(_other);
5254  return Base::DistanceP2(getLocation(), other.getLocation()) <= tol*tol
5255  && getDir().GetAngle(other.getDir()) <= atol
5256  && ((getXDir().GetAngle(other.getXDir()) <= atol
5257  && getYDir().GetAngle(other.getYDir()) <= atol)
5258  // It seems that OCC may change some surface Position (gp_Ax3) to
5259  // right hand coordinate. The following checks is to detect such cases.
5260  || (getXDir().GetAngle(other.getYDir()) <= atol
5261  && getYDir().GetAngle(-other.getXDir()) <= atol)
5262  || (getYDir().GetAngle(other.getXDir()) <= atol
5263  && getXDir().GetAngle(-other.getYDir()) <= atol));
5264 }

5394 
5395 gp_Vec GeomCone::getDN(double u, double v, int Nu, int Nv) const
5396 {
5397  // Will be fixed in OCC 7.7
5398 #if OCC_VERSION_HEX >= 0x070700
5399  return GeomSurface::getDN(u, v, Nu, Nv);
5400 #else
5401  // Copied from ElSLib::ConeDN() and applied the needed fix
5402  auto ElSLib__ConeDN = [](const Standard_Real U,
5403  const Standard_Real V,
5404  const gp_Ax3& Pos,
5405  const Standard_Real Radius,
5406  const Standard_Real SAngle,
5407  const Standard_Integer Nu,
5408  const Standard_Integer Nv)
5409  {
5410  gp_XYZ Xdir = Pos.XDirection().XYZ();
5411  gp_XYZ Ydir = Pos.YDirection().XYZ();
5412  Standard_Real Um = U + Nu * M_PI_2; // M_PI * 0.5
5413  Xdir.Multiply(cos(Um));
5414  Ydir.Multiply(sin(Um));
5415  Xdir.Add(Ydir);
5416  if(Nv == 0) {
5417  Xdir.Multiply(Radius + V * sin(SAngle));
5418  if(Nu == 0) Xdir.Add(Pos.Location().XYZ());
5419  return gp_Vec(Xdir);
5420  }
5421  else if(Nv == 1) {
5422  Xdir.Multiply(sin(SAngle));
5423  if (Nu == 0)
5424  Xdir.Add(Pos.Direction().XYZ() * cos(SAngle));
5425  return gp_Vec(Xdir);
5426  }
5427  return gp_Vec(0.0,0.0,0.0);
5428  };
5429 
5430  // Workaround for cones to get the correct derivatives
5431  // https://forum.freecad.org/viewtopic.php?f=10&t=66677
5432  Handle(Geom_ConicalSurface) s = Handle(Geom_ConicalSurface)::DownCast(handle());
5433  Standard_RangeError_Raise_if (Nu + Nv < 1 || Nu < 0 || Nv < 0, " ");
5434  if (Nv > 1) {
5435  return {0.0, 0.0, 0.0};
5436  }
5437  else {
5438  return ElSLib__ConeDN(u, v, s->Position(), s->RefRadius(), s->SemiAngle(), Nu, Nv);
5439  }
5440 #endif
5441 }
5442

5444 {
5445  return mySurface->RefRadius();
5446 }
5447 
5448 double GeomCone::getSemiAngle() const
5449 {
5450  return mySurface->SemiAngle();
5451 }

5457 }
