5684 bool GeomPlane::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
5685 {
5686  if(_other.getTypeId() != getTypeId()) {
5687  if (_other.isDerivedFrom(GeomSurface::getClassTypeId())) {
5688  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> geo(static_cast<const GeomSurface&>(_other).toPlane());
5689  if (geo)
5690  return isSame(*geo, tol, atol);
5691  }
5692  return false;
5693  }
5694 
5695  auto &other = static_cast<const GeomPlane &>(_other);
5696  return GeomElementarySurface::isSame(other,tol,atol);
5697 }

5760 bool GeomOffsetSurface::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
5761 {
5762  if(_other.getTypeId() != getTypeId())
5763  return false;
5764 
5765  auto &other = static_cast<const GeomOffsetSurface &>(_other);
5766  if(fabs(getOffset() - other.getOffset()) > tol)
5767  return false;
5768 
5769  Handle(Geom_Surface) basis = mySurface->BasisSurface();
5770  Handle(Geom_Surface) basis1 = other.mySurface->BasisSurface();
5771  if(basis.IsNull() || basis1.IsNull() || basis->DynamicType() != basis1->DynamicType())
5772  return false;
5773 
5774  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> b(makeFromSurface(basis));
5775  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> b1(makeFromSurface(basis1));
5776  return b && b1 && b->isSame(*b1,tol,atol);
5777 }

5898 bool GeomTrimmedSurface::isSame(const Geometry &_other, double tol, double atol) const
5899 {
5900  if(_other.getTypeId() != getTypeId())
5901  return false;
5902 
5903  auto &other = static_cast<const GeomTrimmedSurface &>(_other);
5904 
5905  Standard_Real u1[2],u2[2],v1[2],v2[2];
5906  mySurface->Bounds(u1[0],u2[0],v1[0],v2[0]);
5907  other.mySurface->Bounds(u1[1],u2[1],v1[1],v2[1]);
5908 
5909  if(fabs(u1[0]-u1[1])>tol || fabs(u2[0]-u2[1])>tol
5910  || fabs(v1[0]-v1[1])>tol || fabs(v2[0]-v2[1])>tol)
5911  return false;
5912 
5913  Handle(Geom_Surface) basis = mySurface->BasisSurface();
5914  Handle(Geom_Surface) basis1 = other.mySurface->BasisSurface();
5915  if(basis.IsNull() || basis1.IsNull() || basis->DynamicType() != basis1->DynamicType())
5916  return false;
5917 
5918  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> b(makeFromSurface(basis));
5919  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> b1(makeFromSurface(basis1));
5920  return b && b1 && b->isSame(*b1,tol,atol);
5921 }

6074 
6075 // Helper functions for fillet tools
6076 // -------------------------------------------------
6077 namespace Part {
6078 
6079 bool find2DLinesIntersection(const Base::Vector3d &orig1, const Base::Vector3d &dir1,
6080  const Base::Vector3d &orig2, const Base::Vector3d &dir2,
6081  Base::Vector3d &point)
6082 {
6083  double det = dir1.x*dir2.y - dir1.y*dir2.x;
6084  if ((det > 0 ? det : -det) < 1e-10)
6085  return false;
6086  double c1 = dir1.y*orig1.x - dir1.x*orig1.y;
6087  double c2 = dir2.y*orig2.x - dir2.x*orig2.y;
6088  double x = (dir1.x*c2 - dir2.x*c1)/det;
6089  double y = (dir1.y*c2 - dir2.y*c1)/det;
6090  point = Base::Vector3d(x,y,0.f);
6091  return true;
6092 }
6093 
6094 bool find2DLinesIntersection(const GeomLineSegment *lineSeg1, const GeomLineSegment *lineSeg2,
6095  Base::Vector3d &point)
6096 {
6097  Base::Vector3d orig1 = lineSeg1->getStartPoint();
6098  Base::Vector3d orig2 = lineSeg2->getStartPoint();
6099  Base::Vector3d dir1 = (lineSeg1->getEndPoint()-lineSeg1->getStartPoint());
6100  Base::Vector3d dir2 = (lineSeg2->getEndPoint()-lineSeg2->getStartPoint());
6101  return find2DLinesIntersection(orig1, dir1, orig2, dir2, point);
6102 }
6103 
6104 bool findFilletCenter(const GeomLineSegment *lineSeg1, const GeomLineSegment *lineSeg2, double radius,
6105  Base::Vector3d &center)
6106 {
6107  Base::Vector3d midPoint1 = (lineSeg1->getStartPoint()+lineSeg1->getEndPoint())/2;
6108  Base::Vector3d midPoint2 = (lineSeg2->getStartPoint()+lineSeg2->getEndPoint())/2;
6109  return findFilletCenter(lineSeg1, lineSeg2, radius, midPoint1, midPoint2, center);
6110 }
6111 
6112 bool findFilletCenter(const GeomLineSegment *lineSeg1, const GeomLineSegment *lineSeg2, double radius,
6113  const Base::Vector3d &refPnt1, const Base::Vector3d &refPnt2, Base::Vector3d &center)
6114 {
6115  //Calculate directions and normals for each straight line
6116  Base::Vector3d l1p1, l1p2, l2p1, l2p2, dir1, dir2, norm1, norm2;
6117  l1p1 = lineSeg1->getStartPoint();
6118  l1p2 = lineSeg1->getEndPoint();
6119  l2p1 = lineSeg2->getStartPoint();
6120  l2p2 = lineSeg2->getEndPoint();
6121 
6122  dir1 = (l1p1 - l1p2).Normalize();
6123  dir2 = (l2p1 - l2p2).Normalize();
6124 
6125  norm1 = Base::Vector3d(dir1.y, -dir1.x, 0.).Normalize();
6126  norm2 = Base::Vector3d(dir2.y, -dir2.x, 0.).Normalize();
6127 
6128  // calculate the intersections between the normals to find inwards direction
6129 
6130  // find intersection of lines
6131  Base::Vector3d corner;
6132  if (!find2DLinesIntersection(lineSeg1,lineSeg2,corner))
6133  return false;
6134 
6135  // Just project the given reference points onto the lines, just in case they are not already lying on
6136  Base::Vector3d normPnt1, normPnt2;
6137  normPnt1.ProjectToLine(refPnt1-l1p1, l1p2-l1p1);
6138  normPnt2.ProjectToLine(refPnt2-l2p1, l2p2-l2p1);
6139  normPnt1 += refPnt1;
6140  normPnt2 += refPnt2;
6141 
6142  //Angle bisector
6143  Base::Vector3d bisectDir = ((normPnt1 - corner).Normalize() + (normPnt2-corner).Normalize()).Normalize();
6144 
6145  //redefine norms pointing towards bisect line
6146  Base::Vector3d normIntersection1, normIntersection2;
6147  if (find2DLinesIntersection(normPnt1, norm1, corner, bisectDir, normIntersection1) &&
6148  find2DLinesIntersection(normPnt2, norm2, corner, bisectDir, normIntersection2)) {
6149  norm1 = (normIntersection1 - normPnt1).Normalize();
6150  norm2 = (normIntersection2 - normPnt2).Normalize();
6151  } else {
6152  return false;
6153  }
6154 
6155  // Project lines to find mid point of fillet arc
6156  Base::Vector3d tmpPoint1 = l1p1 + (norm1 * radius);
6157  Base::Vector3d tmpPoint2 = l2p1 + (norm2 * radius);
6158 
6159  // found center point
6160  if (find2DLinesIntersection(tmpPoint1, dir1, tmpPoint2, dir2, center))
6161  return true;
6162  else
6163  return false;
6164 }
6165 
6166 // Returns -1 if radius cannot be suggested
6167 double suggestFilletRadius(const GeomLineSegment *lineSeg1, const GeomLineSegment *lineSeg2,
6168  const Base::Vector3d &refPnt1, const Base::Vector3d &refPnt2)
6169 {
6170  Base::Vector3d corner;
6171  if (!Part::find2DLinesIntersection(lineSeg1, lineSeg2, corner))
6172  return -1;
6173 
6174  Base::Vector3d dir1 = lineSeg1->getEndPoint() - lineSeg1->getStartPoint();
6175  Base::Vector3d dir2 = lineSeg2->getEndPoint() - lineSeg2->getStartPoint();
6176 
6177  // Decide the line directions depending on the reference points
6178  if (dir1*(refPnt1-corner) < 0)
6179  dir1 *= -1;
6180  if (dir2*(refPnt2-corner) < 0)
6181  dir2 *= -1;
6182 
6183  //Angle bisector
6184  Base::Vector3d dirBisect = (dir1.Normalize() + dir2.Normalize()).Normalize();
6185 
6186  Base::Vector3d projPnt1, projPnt2;
6187  projPnt1.ProjectToLine(refPnt1-corner, dir1);
6188  projPnt2.ProjectToLine(refPnt2-corner, dir2);
6189  projPnt1 += refPnt1;
6190  projPnt2 += refPnt2;
6191 
6192  Base::Vector3d norm1(dir1.y, -dir1.x, 0.f);
6193  Base::Vector3d norm2(dir2.y, -dir2.x, 0.f);
6194 
6195  double r1=-1, r2=-1;
6196  Base::Vector3d center1, center2;
6197  if (find2DLinesIntersection(projPnt1, norm1, corner, dirBisect, center1))
6198  r1 = (projPnt1 - center1).Length();
6199  if (find2DLinesIntersection(projPnt2, norm2, corner, dirBisect, center2))
6200  r2 = (projPnt1 - center2).Length();
6201 
6202  return r1 < r2 ? r1 : r2;
6203 }
6204 
6205 GeomArcOfCircle *createFilletGeometry(const GeomLineSegment *lineSeg1, const GeomLineSegment *lineSeg2,
6206  const Base::Vector3d &center, double radius)
6207 {
6208  Base::Vector3d corner;
6209  if (!Part::find2DLinesIntersection(lineSeg1, lineSeg2, corner))
6210  // Parallel Lines so return null pointer
6211  return nullptr;
6212 
6213  Base::Vector3d dir1 = lineSeg1->getEndPoint() - lineSeg1->getStartPoint();
6214  Base::Vector3d dir2 = lineSeg2->getEndPoint() - lineSeg2->getStartPoint();
6215 
6216  Base::Vector3d radDir1, radDir2;
6217  radDir1.ProjectToLine(center - corner, dir1);
6218  radDir2.ProjectToLine(center - corner, dir2);
6219 
6220  // Angle Variables
6221  double startAngle, endAngle, range;
6222 
6223  startAngle = atan2(radDir1.y, radDir1.x);
6224  range = atan2(-radDir1.y*radDir2.x+radDir1.x*radDir2.y,
6225  radDir1.x*radDir2.x+radDir1.y*radDir2.y);
6226  endAngle = startAngle + range;
6227 
6228  if (endAngle < startAngle)
6229  std::swap(startAngle, endAngle);
6230 
6231  if (endAngle > 2*M_PI )
6232  endAngle -= 2*M_PI;
6233 
6234  if (startAngle < 0 )
6235  endAngle += 2*M_PI;
6236 
6237  // Create Arc Segment
6238  GeomArcOfCircle *arc = new GeomArcOfCircle();
6239  arc->setRadius(radius);
6240  arc->setCenter(center);
6241  arc->setRange(startAngle, endAngle, /*emulateCCWXY=*/true);
6242 
6243  return arc;
6244 }
6245 
6246 std::unique_ptr<GeomSurface> makeFromSurface(const Handle(Geom_Surface)& s, bool silent)
6247 {
6248  std::unique_ptr<GeomSurface> geoSurf;
6249 
6250  if (s.IsNull()) {
6251  if (!silent)
6252  throw Base::ValueError("Null surface");
6253  return geoSurf;
6254  }
6255 
6256  if (s->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_ToroidalSurface))) {

6313 std::unique_ptr<GeomSurface> makeFromSurfaceAdaptor(const BRepAdaptor_Surface& adapt, bool silent)
6314 {
6315  std::unique_ptr<GeomSurface> geoSurf;
6316 
6317  switch(adapt.GetType())
6318  {
6319  case GeomAbs_Plane:
6320  {
6321  geoSurf.reset(new GeomPlane());
6322  Handle(Geom_Plane) this_surf = Handle(Geom_Plane)::DownCast
6323  (geoSurf->handle());
6324  this_surf->SetPln(adapt.Plane());
6325  break;
6326  }
6327  case GeomAbs_Cylinder:
6328  {
6329  geoSurf.reset(new GeomCylinder());
6330  Handle(Geom_CylindricalSurface) this_surf = Handle(Geom_CylindricalSurface)::DownCast
6331  (geoSurf->handle());
6332  this_surf->SetCylinder(adapt.Cylinder());
6333  break;
6334  }
6335  case GeomAbs_Cone:
6336  {
6337  geoSurf.reset(new GeomCone());
6338  Handle(Geom_ConicalSurface) this_surf = Handle(Geom_ConicalSurface)::DownCast
6339  (geoSurf->handle());
6340  this_surf->SetCone(adapt.Cone());
6341  break;
6342  }
6343  case GeomAbs_Sphere:
6344  {
6345  geoSurf.reset(new GeomSphere());
6346  Handle(Geom_SphericalSurface) this_surf = Handle(Geom_SphericalSurface)::DownCast
6347  (geoSurf->handle());
6348  this_surf->SetSphere(adapt.Sphere());
6349  break;
6350  }
6351  case GeomAbs_Torus:
6352  {
6353  geoSurf.reset(new GeomToroid());
6354  Handle(Geom_ToroidalSurface) this_surf = Handle(Geom_ToroidalSurface)::DownCast
6355  (geoSurf->handle());
6356  this_surf->SetTorus(adapt.Torus());
6357  break;
6358  }
6359  case GeomAbs_BezierSurface:
6360  {
6361  geoSurf.reset(new GeomBezierSurface(adapt.Bezier()));
6362  break;
6363  }
6364  case GeomAbs_BSplineSurface:
6365  {
6366  geoSurf.reset(new GeomBSplineSurface(adapt.BSpline()));
6367  break;
6368  }
6369  case GeomAbs_SurfaceOfRevolution:
6370  {
6371  Handle(Geom_Surface) s = BRep_Tool::Surface(adapt.Face());
6372  Handle(Geom_SurfaceOfRevolution) rev = Handle(Geom_SurfaceOfRevolution)::DownCast(s);
6373  if (rev.IsNull()) {
6374  Handle(Geom_RectangularTrimmedSurface) rect = Handle(Geom_RectangularTrimmedSurface)::DownCast(s);
6375  rev = Handle(Geom_SurfaceOfRevolution)::DownCast(rect->BasisSurface());
6376  }
6377  if (!rev.IsNull())
6378  geoSurf.reset(new GeomSurfaceOfRevolution(rev));
6379  break;
6380  }
6381  case GeomAbs_SurfaceOfExtrusion:
6382  {
6383  Handle(Geom_Surface) s = BRep_Tool::Surface(adapt.Face());
6384  Handle(Geom_SurfaceOfLinearExtrusion) ext = Handle(Geom_SurfaceOfLinearExtrusion)::DownCast(s);
6385  if (ext.IsNull()) {
6386  Handle(Geom_RectangularTrimmedSurface) rect = Handle(Geom_RectangularTrimmedSurface)::DownCast(s);
6387  ext = Handle(Geom_SurfaceOfLinearExtrusion)::DownCast(rect->BasisSurface());
6388  }
6389  if (!ext.IsNull())
6390  geoSurf.reset(new GeomSurfaceOfExtrusion(ext));
6391  break;
6392  }
6393  case GeomAbs_OffsetSurface:
6394  {
6395  Handle(Geom_Surface) s = BRep_Tool::Surface(adapt.Face());
6396  Handle(Geom_OffsetSurface) off = Handle(Geom_OffsetSurface)::DownCast(s);
6397  if (off.IsNull()) {
6398  Handle(Geom_RectangularTrimmedSurface) rect = Handle(Geom_RectangularTrimmedSurface)::DownCast(s);
6399  off = Handle(Geom_OffsetSurface)::DownCast(rect->BasisSurface());
6400  }
6401  if (!off.IsNull())
6402  geoSurf.reset(new GeomOffsetSurface(off));
6403  break;
6404  }
6405  default:
6406  break;
6407  }
6408 
6409  if (!geoSurf && !silent) {
6410  std::string err = "Cannot convert surface type ";
6411  Handle(Geom_Surface) s = BRep_Tool::Surface(adapt.Face());
6412  if (s)
6413  err += s->DynamicType()->Name();
6414  else
6415  err += " unknown";
6416  throw Base::TypeError(err);
6417  }
6418 
6419  return geoSurf;
6420 }

6423 std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve> makeFromCurve(const Handle(Geom_Curve)& c, bool silent)
6424 {
6425  std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve> geoCurve;
6426 
6427  if (c.IsNull()) {
6428  if (!silent)
6429  throw Base::ValueError("Null curve");
6430  return geoCurve;
6431  }
6432 
6433  if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_Circle))) {
6434  Handle(Geom_Circle) circ = Handle(Geom_Circle)::DownCast(c);
6435  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomCircle>(circ);
6436  }
6437  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_Ellipse))) {
6438  Handle(Geom_Ellipse) ell = Handle(Geom_Ellipse)::DownCast(c);
6439  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomEllipse>(ell);
6440  }
6441  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_Hyperbola))) {
6442  Handle(Geom_Hyperbola) hyp = Handle(Geom_Hyperbola)::DownCast(c);
6443  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomHyperbola>(hyp);
6444  }
6445  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_Line))) {
6446  Handle(Geom_Line) lin = Handle(Geom_Line)::DownCast(c);
6447  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomLine>(lin);
6448  }
6449  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_OffsetCurve))) {
6450  Handle(Geom_OffsetCurve) oc = Handle(Geom_OffsetCurve)::DownCast(c);
6451  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomOffsetCurve>(oc);
6452  }
6453  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_Parabola))) {
6454  Handle(Geom_Parabola) par = Handle(Geom_Parabola)::DownCast(c);
6455  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomParabola>(par);
6456  }
6457  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_TrimmedCurve))) {
6458  return makeFromTrimmedCurve(c, c->FirstParameter(), c->LastParameter());
6459  }
6460  /*else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_BoundedCurve))) {
6461  Handle(Geom_BoundedCurve) bc = Handle(Geom_BoundedCurve)::DownCast(c);
6462  return Py::asObject(new GeometryCurvePy(new GeomBoundedCurve(bc)));
6463  }*/
6464  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_BezierCurve))) {
6465  Handle(Geom_BezierCurve) bezier = Handle(Geom_BezierCurve)::DownCast(c);
6466  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomBezierCurve>(bezier);
6467  }
6468  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_BSplineCurve))) {
6469  Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve) bspline = Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve)::DownCast(c);
6470  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomBSplineCurve>(bspline);
6471  }
6472  else {
6473  std::string err = "Unhandled curve type ";
6474  err += c->DynamicType()->Name();
6475  throw Base::TypeError(err);
6476  }
6477 
6478  return geoCurve;
6479 }

6481 std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve> makeFromTrimmedCurve(const Handle(Geom_Curve)& c, double f, double l, bool silent)
6482 {
6483  if (c.IsNull()) {
6484  if (!silent)
6485  throw Base::ValueError("Null curve");
6486  return std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve>();
6487  }
6488 
6489  if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_Circle))) {
6490  Handle(Geom_Circle) circ = Handle(Geom_Circle)::DownCast(c);
6491  std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve> arc(new GeomArcOfCircle());
6492  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) this_arc = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast
6493  (arc->handle());
6494  Handle(Geom_Circle) this_circ = Handle(Geom_Circle)::DownCast
6495  (this_arc->BasisCurve());
6496  this_circ->SetCirc(circ->Circ());
6497  this_arc->SetTrim(f, l);
6498  return arc;
6499  }
6500  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_Ellipse))) {
6501  Handle(Geom_Ellipse) ellp = Handle(Geom_Ellipse)::DownCast(c);
6502  std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve> arc(new GeomArcOfEllipse());
6503  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) this_arc = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast
6504  (arc->handle());
6505  Handle(Geom_Ellipse) this_ellp = Handle(Geom_Ellipse)::DownCast
6506  (this_arc->BasisCurve());
6507  this_ellp->SetElips(ellp->Elips());
6508  this_arc->SetTrim(f, l);
6509  return arc;
6510  }
6511  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_Hyperbola))) {
6512  Handle(Geom_Hyperbola) hypr = Handle(Geom_Hyperbola)::DownCast(c);
6513  std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve> arc(new GeomArcOfHyperbola());
6514  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) this_arc = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast
6515  (arc->handle());
6516  Handle(Geom_Hyperbola) this_hypr = Handle(Geom_Hyperbola)::DownCast
6517  (this_arc->BasisCurve());
6518  this_hypr->SetHypr(hypr->Hypr());
6519  this_arc->SetTrim(f, l);
6520  return arc;
6521  }
6522  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_Line))) {
6523  Handle(Geom_Line) line = Handle(Geom_Line)::DownCast(c);
6524  std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve> segm(new GeomLineSegment());
6525  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) this_segm = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast
6526  (segm->handle());
6527  Handle(Geom_Line) this_line = Handle(Geom_Line)::DownCast
6528  (this_segm->BasisCurve());
6529  this_line->SetLin(line->Lin());
6530  this_segm->SetTrim(f, l);
6531  return segm;
6532  }
6533  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_Parabola))) {
6534  Handle(Geom_Parabola) para = Handle(Geom_Parabola)::DownCast(c);
6535  std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve> arc(new GeomArcOfParabola());
6536  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) this_arc = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast
6537  (arc->handle());
6538  Handle(Geom_Parabola) this_para = Handle(Geom_Parabola)::DownCast
6539  (this_arc->BasisCurve());
6540  this_para->SetParab(para->Parab());
6541  this_arc->SetTrim(f, l);
6542  return arc;
6543  }
6544  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_BezierCurve))) {
6545  Handle(Geom_BezierCurve) bezier = Handle(Geom_BezierCurve)::DownCast(c->Copy());
6546  bezier->Segment(f, l);
6547  return std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve>(new GeomBezierCurve(bezier));
6548  }
6549  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_BSplineCurve))) {
6550  Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve) bspline = Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve)::DownCast(c->Copy());
6551  bspline->Segment(f, l);
6552  return std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve>(new GeomBSplineCurve(bspline));
6553  }
6554  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_OffsetCurve))) {
6555  Handle(Geom_OffsetCurve) oc = Handle(Geom_OffsetCurve)::DownCast(c);
6556  double v = oc->Offset();
6557  gp_Dir dir = oc->Direction();
6558  std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve> bc(makeFromTrimmedCurve(oc->BasisCurve(), f, l));
6559  return std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve>(new GeomOffsetCurve(Handle(Geom_Curve)::DownCast(bc->handle()), v, dir));
6560  }
6561  else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_TrimmedCurve))) {
6562  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) trc = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast(c);
6563  return makeFromTrimmedCurve(trc->BasisCurve(), f, l);
6564  }
6565  /*else if (c->IsKind(STANDARD_TYPE(Geom_BoundedCurve))) {
6566  Handle(Geom_BoundedCurve) bc = Handle(Geom_BoundedCurve)::DownCast(c);
6567  return Py::asObject(new GeometryCurvePy(new GeomBoundedCurve(bc)));
6568  }*/
6569  else if (!silent) {
6570  std::string err = "Unhandled curve type ";
6571  err += c->DynamicType()->Name();
6572  throw Base::TypeError(err);
6573  }
6574 
6575  return std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve>();
6576 }
6577 
6578 std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve> makeFromCurveAdaptor(const Adaptor3d_Curve& adapt, bool silent)
6579 {
6580  std::unique_ptr<GeomCurve> geoCurve;
6581  switch (adapt.GetType())
6582  {
6583  case GeomAbs_Line:
6584  {
6585  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomLine>();
6586  Handle(Geom_Line) this_curv = Handle(Geom_Line)::DownCast
6587  (geoCurve->handle());
6588  this_curv->SetLin(adapt.Line());
6589  break;
6590  }
6591  case GeomAbs_Circle:
6592  {
6593  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomCircle>();
6594  Handle(Geom_Circle) this_curv = Handle(Geom_Circle)::DownCast
6595  (geoCurve->handle());
6596  this_curv->SetCirc(adapt.Circle());
6597  break;
6598  }
6599  case GeomAbs_Ellipse:
6600  {
6601  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomEllipse>();
6602  Handle(Geom_Ellipse) this_curv = Handle(Geom_Ellipse)::DownCast
6603  (geoCurve->handle());
6604  this_curv->SetElips(adapt.Ellipse());
6605  break;
6606  }
6607  case GeomAbs_Hyperbola:
6608  {
6609  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomHyperbola>();
6610  Handle(Geom_Hyperbola) this_curv = Handle(Geom_Hyperbola)::DownCast
6611  (geoCurve->handle());
6612  this_curv->SetHypr(adapt.Hyperbola());
6613  break;
6614  }
6615  case GeomAbs_Parabola:
6616  {
6617  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomParabola>();
6618  Handle(Geom_Parabola) this_curv = Handle(Geom_Parabola)::DownCast
6619  (geoCurve->handle());
6620  this_curv->SetParab(adapt.Parabola());
6621  break;
6622  }
6623  case GeomAbs_BezierCurve:
6624  {
6625  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomBezierCurve>(adapt.Bezier());
6626  break;
6627  }
6628  case GeomAbs_BSplineCurve:
6629  {
6630  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomBSplineCurve>(adapt.BSpline());
6631  break;
6632  }
6633  case GeomAbs_OffsetCurve:
6634  {
6635  geoCurve = std::make_unique<GeomOffsetCurve>(adapt.OffsetCurve());
6636  break;
6637  }
6638  case GeomAbs_OtherCurve:
6639  default:
6640  break;
6641  }
6642 
6643  if (!geoCurve) {
6644  if (!silent)
6645  throw Base::TypeError("Unhandled curve type");
6646  return geoCurve;
6647  }
6648 
6649  // Check if the curve must be trimmed
6650  Handle(Geom_Curve) curv3d = Handle(Geom_Curve)::DownCast
6651  (geoCurve->handle());
6652  double u = curv3d->FirstParameter();
6653  double v = curv3d->LastParameter();
6654  if (u != adapt.FirstParameter() || v != adapt.LastParameter()) {
6655  geoCurve = makeFromTrimmedCurve(curv3d, adapt.FirstParameter(), adapt.LastParameter());
6656  }
6657 
6658  return geoCurve;
6659 }
